{"text": "Extremely fun grotesque game where you are the monster, and you go though-out the levels  devouring all enemies in your path and growing while attempting to escape a facality.  Its entire story is done though show don't tell which is nice, and allows for some interpretation and theory crafting which is nice.  It is well worth the price but keep in mind it is a extremely short game. I have put 11 hours into this game and have 100% but i may come back to play it again just for fun and enjoyment as it is an enjoyable game to play while waiting or doing other stuff.    I would say it could take about 7 hours to 100% first time, a lot of my time was me having the game open while doing other stuff.   and speed-running or runs after  that can be done much quicker. .The controls are nice-fluid and simple. Pro Great graphic style. Satisfying and relaxing to play. Can be played at any time as a quick time waster. Interesting level design and puzzles.  multiple ways to play and abilties to diverse and choice your play style.  I have watched 3 others play it and the all played differently. some more stealthy others really agressive.  cons:  way too short.. i want to play way more (i hope they released DLC, and offer mod support for modders to make their own levels and storys.) depositing mechanic I like the idea and enjoy it to have to use other abiltiies you have to deposit your mass to become smaller.   But i often find myself running back and fourth between rooms way too often to go collect and deposit the mass and it can become somewhat tedious, especially after beating the game and going back for collectables while exploring.  enemies don't respawn.. once they are dead they are dead.. i wish i could load up my old save i 100% and go around and just replay levels fully upgraded.. but they are so lifeless after you have been though them wrecking carnage. I wish their was a way to respawn enemies as i would like to run around and kill stuff again.  9/10 Love it, wish their was more.. great for the price.", "appid": "953490", "steamid": "profiles/76561198034856633", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1595764800.0}
