{"text": "I'd like to point out I never played call of duty zombies on a PROPER platform, my only experience with it was playing it on mobile.  This dlc in my opinion is almost worth its pricetag, these are remastered maps afterall. However, the graphical enhancement is on point. lighting adds to the atmosphere and colour selection is exquisiste. I imagine reliving these maps must be quite the nostalgia trip for veteran zombie slayers. I recommend this dlc, but the only caviat to this is the hefty price of the base game, and my opinion on that game is a mixed bag. I did buy this game only for the dlc, and as a person who bought the wii u only for smash bros and bayonetta 2, i'd say this zombie dlc alone is not worth the full price, however, if you are as keen as I was to experience the zombie shooter that once was, then go for it, you will not be dissapointed. Just make sure you have some friends and/or a solid wifi connection for mulitplayer. Playing zombies solo becomes boring after 20 minutes.  8.7/10", "appid": "581450", "steamid": "profiles/76561198067218328", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1500465600.0}
