{"text": "Total War Saga: Thrones of Britannia After completing a short campaign with Dyflin (Dublin) on Legendary Difficulty i'm very suprised, but in a good way. As far as i know both, ToB and ATTILA, use the same engin, so i first thought that ToB would have very poor performance like it was the case in ATTILA, but it's the opposide: very good graphic AND performance !!! (even in huge battles). So i guess Creative Assembly found a way to fix it. The campaign adds new features, for example how the technology system works or that you don't have to build recrutement buildings anymore to be able to recrute troops. But there are some things i don't like and these points are important. A campaign is easy to complete if you survived the early game and built up a good strength. You could use mods though to create more of a challenge. - Good Graphics - Good Performance - Awesome Setting/Time Period - Awesome Units (balance and design) - Awesome Siege Battles - AWESOME SOUNDTRACK - New Game Mechanics (good/bad) - No Naval Battles (only transports) - No Ambushing Battles - No Village Garrisons My Review: 6.5/10", "appid": "712100", "steamid": "profiles/76561198163740808", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "77", "votes_funny": "4", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1525348800.0}
