{"text": "I haven't played for very long (and therefore can't comment on the storyline), but here are some first impressions for the digital standard edition. 1) the graphics are good and the setting is beautiful (especially the *relatively deserted* islands). 2) ship/sea combat is amazing. 3) PIRATES!!!??!!! 4) general combat is ... it's ok, but the sneaking and hiding features are decent. 5) the controls... here's where i have an issue. Frankly speaking, you need to use a controller to get the most out of this game IMO. \"Free-running\" is the same as sprinting, so unless you want to walk at a snail's pace you'll need to use that   BUT, the free-running part will always assume you want to climb a wall if you run into it by accident (which wastes your time)... meaning that your target gets away. It's pretty annoying but there's nothing you can do about it as you HAVE to RUN after your target, not walk. But overall it seems like a pretty good game. Though i'd only recommend it if it's on sale.", "appid": "242050", "steamid": "profiles/76561198018827033", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "10", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1528459200.0}
