{"text": "Insurgency: Sandstorm is a successful prequel to Insurgency (2014).  First off, you have the same point gamemodes, new gamemodes (domination, frenzy), and a ton more weapons for your disposal.  Secondly, the game did have a rocky start, with performance and optimization issues, but the devs worked around them.  With new content like modding, more weapons and maps, and new cosmetic items coming to the game, I think I'll give this one a thumbs up. The experience may be a bit more \"arcade\" than Source, but only if you choose the casual modes. Overall, Sandstorm is a good experience for people interested in semi-realistic military shooters (more fun and no roleplay like Arma 3) taking place in the Middle East.", "appid": "581320", "steamid": "profiles/76561198100756168", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1578398400.0}
