{"text": "Content warning: murder, stalking, obsessive infatuation, suicide, physical abuse references, sexual assault, psychotic behavior, gaslighting, abduction, and general scenes regarding death. This game has psychological horror and a murder mystery (though, none of it is graphic). The protagonist goes on a university class trip to a remote island with a professor and some classmates. After one night, a murder occurs and suddenly everyone is suspicious. Meanwhile, there are three guys the protagonist can become romantically involved with despite the situation.  Sadly, it involves what I call \"psycho romance\" in which a romantic interest character is so deeply infatuated with a protagonist that they do absolutely bat-sh*t crazy things to secure their involvement with said protagonist. I understand that some people like this and understand that it is fictional or a fantasy.   I suppose I understand the psychology of it as feeling so wanted that someone is willing to do crazy things for you, but at the same time, that same person can do crazy things   you as well. Furthermore, no one is   to you, no matter what they've done for you. Why am I still giving it a positive review? Because the psychotic behavior is framed negatively, at least. The story is still entertaining and I really liked the other romance paths.  It's a decent VN with two decent romance paths and, I guess, if you're into psycho romance, obviously, you'd like it.", "appid": "710950", "steamid": "profiles/76561198067189801", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1602763200.0}
