{"text": "It sucks that the online servers are gone. You can set this up for LAN play fairly easily with modern LAN-over-internet software; but the original multiplayer allowed for casual and ad-hoc drop-in/drop-out sessions. This is a pretty nice ARPG that competes with the current best ARPGs in a few ways:  * Large variety and variance in stats for dropped loot, and your character has quite a few equip slots. When you think the game has settled into a level-by-level grind, it will drop an item that exceeds anything you've seen before.  * Properly flexible character builds. It is possible to mess up and develop a character that just can't handle the higher difficulty levels.  In that case, I think you are stuck. But the flipside of this is that the game really gives you choice and control. You usually need to spread your skill points between skills that make you more powerful and skills that reduce your cooldowns.  * Nice open-world map. This is closer to Skyrim than Diablo 3. NPCs carry out day-to-day activities, monsters fight with the guards at town gates, end exploring the world map is rewarding in itself.", "appid": "225640", "steamid": "profiles/76561198078127217", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1564574400.0}
