{"text": "This game is definitely in the alpha stage, but that's OK. Given the very low price and the fact that it comes with Steam trading cards, it's worth picking up even if you don't plan on playing it. That said, it has a lot of potential. The world looks nice, though I'm sure it'll be expanded and improved upon. At the moment, you can walk/run around it, but I couldn't interact with any objects, jump, or adjust settings. There were places I got \"stuck\" because I could step down into them but I could not get back out or move around it since there was no jumping possible. Suggested changes/improvements: Expand the world Enable interaction with objects in the game world Allow users to adjust the mouse sensitivity (the sensitivity is MUCH lower than most gamers would like) Enable jumping/firing/action keys Lock the cursor into the window Maybe allow players to interact with one another in some way to make it more \"real\" and personal than just seeing another player's soul Allow an in-game menu, rather than the Escape key automatically kicking you out of the game All in all, it needs quite a bit of work but is definitely worth picking up if you can get it cheaply. I will probably play it a lot more once the developers polish it more and add in some of those features I listed or put more in the game to do. Go ahead and get it while it's cheap. I'm sure if they put a lot more into the game it won't be under a dollar.", "appid": "400250", "steamid": "profiles/76561197976116287", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1451822400.0}
