{"text": "is a first-person shooter that mixes fast-paced combat with an ever-increasing difficulty steep and platforming to navigate the terrain. The game's main idea appears to be always to keep moving and is an action title that features a crazy amount of weapon and weak points to exploit in your enemies. There is a lot of detail to appreciate in its gameplay and is one of the best first-person shooters. If you are interested in slaying demons at high speed and enjoy crazy good shooting, keep reading! In   enemies have weak points that can be exploited to either make them easier to kill or disable a capacity in them, such as long-range weaponry. The attention to detail here is astounding, as you keep searching for these during combat and start to learn their weaknesses. Targeting a weak point is the difference between killing a demon with few bullets or an entire magazine! It is satisfactory, too, as you get to hear a \"bing\" sound every time you hit a weak point. This mixed with the game's high-speed pace makes it like an adrenaline-filled experience in which you must shoot lots of demons while also trying to search for windows to exploit their weak points. The maps are filled with pickups to obtain and platforming so you can navigate around while in combat. It is so fast that at first, it was hard for me to keep up, but you eventually get used to it and start to become better while playing, so it has a steep learning curve and just went it starts to become comfortable, it adds new enemies or mechanics to keep you in your toes. I wouldn't say I liked the system for weapon switching as I found it to be quite awkward in my opinion, you can only go back between the last two weapons you selected previously. Besides, you have to open a wheel to select any of the other guns, and while time does slow down during it, my take on it is like navigating a menu mid-combat. Since there are many tools to use, I would have preferred a more intuitive and straightforward system to select them. Speaking of the different weapons, one of the things that impressed me the most is an absolute bonkers number of upgrades and mods! There were so many that I did not know what to choose at times and are very useful! You can turn a shotgun into an automatic terror that keeps going until it is dry or add grenade launchers so demons can chew on them while you kill them. There are also upgrades to the suit, which can help you locate things in your map or lower your abilities recharge. The campaign is replayable, and there are many reasons to play it again, from collecting all collectibles to getting all upgrades. They also added twists to make it more attractive on a second run, such as cheat codes that can influence the gameplay or different modes such as arcade with lives. It can be exhausting to play at times, as I did suffer a bit of fatigue, with some missions being able to last 20-40 minutes. During my time with the title, I would usually play sessions of 1-2 tasks and then pause to make this more tolerable; I don't mind them being long, however. Also, I don't particularly appreciate that platforming seems to be implemented oddly in some sections, like having to break a wall. Simultaneously, it can sometimes lead to falling off, or some jumping platforms can make you lose momentum if you dash. The strong point of   is that it is a first-person shooter with tons of things to discover. There are many challenges, secrets, and exploration to do, and should you do; Then you can be rewarded with upgrades or weapons to add to your arsenal! It adds an extra layer to shooters with the addition of chainsaw enemies to recover armor and have to pay attention to details to come victorious in its vicious combat! Executions have gore visuals into them, and with the high-speed chaotic formula, it doesn't get dull at any moment save some platforming bits. The weak point of this title is that there is no incentive to try the more formidable difficulties. During my playthrough, I choose the one after what would be considered normal, but there was no reason to go beyond that. There are no achievements or significant rewards for beating the game at the max difficulty, and I think this can take some of that replayability I mentioned before. The story did not impress me either, as it boils down to you, killing demons while higher demons tell you to stop, and you ignore them. It could have been more interesting if we had a more interactive main cast, perhaps. It was tested on an RTX 2070 S, during my experience as of this review; there were no crashes. I would have loved if the chainsaw ran out of fuel as you use it rather than being an automatic cleave, as that could make it more gore like while adding skill to using it! There are tactics the game doesn't tell you as burning a demon before executing it still gives you armor to pick up or that you can hook to a monster, and instead of shooting it, chainsaw him to get ammo while traveling long distances. Ammunition being colorful in contrast to the blood theme of the world of   is amusing and looks sick, so I appreciate that detail!  is an outstanding title with one of the best shooting I have experienced in gaming, It is a superb title with almost no flaws and adds diverse layers to an established genre. There is a lot to do while exploring the levels it features, and its gameplay is always filled with adrenaline and the exhibition of how good you can be while playing it. I had a great time with it as I went from being scare of demons to punching them out of existence! If you like this review, give it a thumbs up! If you want to add your own opinion or share something informative, do it below in the comments!", "appid": "782330", "steamid": "profiles/76561198134319796", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "109", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1598443200.0}
