{"text": "Space chess video game. At Hard level, the game really felt like chess. I love chess! You've got 3 very different units (= a squad) and try to survive (and fill important secondary objectives) with their different abilities, as enemies pop up every turn. I often spent 5 minutes studying a turn/move in this game. Best thing is it has always paid off, as there's often a better solution than the obvious one. Game is rich, clever, balanced and everything is well explained, even at the firt run ; you can be \"unlucky\", but with strong and a thoughtful planning (at every turn) you should be alright. Also, I don't know how they did it : you're constantly about to lose, but there's always a way out. This makes this game exciting all along. After 6 hours, I finished a run with one of the 10 different squads - obviously, a different squad implies a totally different run, as you could even run with the same squad several times. I like where it tickled my brain, I'm horny now : 9/10", "appid": "590380", "steamid": "profiles/76561198002405711", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1553169600.0}
