{"text": "I'll start off by saying this game is truly spectacular. I had heard of the hype this was receiving prior to its release, but did not pay much attention to it. However, after seeing some gameplay videos I thought it would be a decent purchase.  It definitely surpasses 'decent.' The amount of content you get for what you pay is substantial. The Tutorial area itself is about 8 hours long (White Orchard) and is a very good way to start out the game. The later areas are all unique and varied, with their own music for their atmosphere. For example, Novigrad, the city, has a very happy-styled music, whereas the Velen region features a quite depressing one. I think my favourite area is Skellige because of its classic fantasy look to it, feeling more suited to the game's genre. While the combat is not amazing, the higher difficulties make you play how you're meant to play - utilising the bombs, potions and oils to defeat your opponents. It is a better experience on the higher difficulties - however the beginning of the game will be harder than the rest of it, as starting out you have limited potions and only the basic oils. People like to compare The Witcher 3 with Skyrim. In my opinion, it's like comparing apples and oranges. While they're both 'fruit' so to speak, they are quite different. Skyrim's focus is on exploration and immersion, The Witcher, while having some exploring in there, does not emphasize it and instead has a priority focus on the story, which does engange you from the very beginning to the end. Bear in mind, I have yet to finish this game at the time of writing this review, and I'm 90 hours in. The sidequests are abundant and interesting, no fetch quests, each are quite unique and fun, sometimes linking to the story. The Witcher Contracts are extremely fun, tracking down powerful monsters which are usually on par with your level so as to keep the fight interesting. Overall, I think The Witcher 3 has lived up to its hype and it deserves a 10/10", "appid": "292030", "steamid": "profiles/76561197982969880", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "17", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1435492800.0}
