{"text": "This mod and its community is pretty great. Joined a clan back in 2010 and nearly 9 years later that clan is now the community im leading. To fully experiance this mod in the best possible way here are some advices: 1. Community events. These are events such as linebattle, Pugs and siege and they are the best way to experiance this mod. They are usually hosted at specific times and there are steamgroups for them with further info and rules and such. 2. Talk to the people. Getting to know the community is important. 3. Join a clan. Joining a clan is a great idea if you enjoy playing the mod and maybe wanna become a bit better at it or you just want a greater challenge. Clan vs Clan battles can be anything from 5v5 smaller matches to huge linebattles. You also may end up in a clan where you feel like you dont fit in but you can always change clan until you find the group of people that makes your experiance better. I hope this helps // General Skill of 42Cdo", "appid": "1057700", "steamid": "profiles/76561197969948521", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "22", "votes_funny": "6", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1562068800.0}
{"text": "Team Fortress 2 will always have a special place in my heart. I will always come back to playing this game no matter if it's been a month or a year.  The community is definitely the best part of Team Fortress 2, this was where I found most of my Steam Friends. The Steam Workshop still receives new and exciting cosmetics, skins and weapon ideas. Some of these should be included into the game, but Valve have started to really take their time with updates so unfortunately there is a high likelihood that they won't be added into the game. There are casual, competitive and community servers. Nobody plays competitive anymore and most casual servers are played on 2Fort usually containing a raging gibus sniper, a script kiddy, pyros doing the conga in the sewers, and that one scunt that tryhards the objective. The community servers are when the game gets interesting. Anything that you can think of playing, Deathrun, Hightower but with extra tower, 2Fort but it's only forts, WarioWare, and even Slender Man. There is so much mayhem and mindless fun, you will likely lose track of time and play until 3am. Team Fortress 2 is a great game and I strongly recommend it, however it deserves more love and care from Valve. 9.7/10", "appid": "440", "steamid": "profiles/76561198276183501", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1499860800.0}
