{"text": "In Murdered: Soul Suspect you follow the story of Detective Ronan O'Connor. He gets killed out of the blue and wants to find out who killed him and why. Because you're dead, you find yourself in Dusk, the limbo world. Using your new supernatural abilities you explore Salem the small little town you used to live in. The main mechanic of the game, and what you'll be doing the most is going from location to location and explore them for clues, and eventually try to string them together to find out what happened. Each location will bring you a bit closer to you're own mystery. Finding these clues is as simple as just walking around the place and pressing a button on items of interest. If you have enough clues, you can try to conclude the research by clicking the correct memories that belong together. This will then lead you to a small cut scene showing what happened. The game is mostly based on cut scenes as well, which in my opinion is perfect. The game also is about the perfect length, not to long and not to short(about 6-7 hours if you don't go for collectibles). Characters you encounter are interesting, and each of them contribute to the story in their own way. Speaking about the story, it's interesting and keeps you engaged throughout the game. Some nice twists keep it refreshing and make you want to know what's next. This together with good voice acting and decent graphics make up for a well-rounded and interesting game.  That doesn't mean there are no cons though. I personally had some optimization issues on both my laptop and desktop. I had to turn down the graphics quite a bit to get a smooth frame rate, even though I have 2 quite powerful systems.  The game also at times throws some demons into the mix, you need to either avoid those, or destroy them. Personally I never looked encountering them, and they felt kind off forced... to get some more diversity in there or something.  Camera controls are also a bit clunky at times, but nothing to bad.  In the end, I would highly recommend Murdered: Soul Suspect to anyone who likes story driven games. It's a solid and interesting detective game.", "appid": "233290", "steamid": "profiles/76561198027163572", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "24", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1583755200.0}
