{"text": "This is a really fun Xcom game situated in the fifties. I love the fifties setting, nice graphics for an old game. Health tips: Let go of the turn based Xcom games and all of its established features. Embrace the action packed third person viewed battles. Use the super slow motion feature to control your two Xcom colleagues and use your and their special skills. Your colleagues have a mind of their own and will act and move but will try to listen to all your commands and even ask for them. Immerse yourself in the story and look at this game as a special not-standard Xcom game. I finished it in 26-ish hours which is rather fast, because for me it was really captivating. Little tip: try easy mode and enjoy the fascinating story and actually good battles. Choose your difficulty with care, this little gem can really kick your buttocks. It totally surprised me how much I would like this game. I'd like more of this in a future Xcom game. Should you see it on sale, don't hesitate. If you like immersive story driven action with interesting progression in skills and gear and you're not afraid to look around for things to discover and you have a modicum of patience, well then... Get yourself some popcorn and a drink, have a seat, dim the lights and... Enjoy.", "appid": "65930", "steamid": "profiles/76561198016780868", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "24", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1601121600.0}
