{"text": "Devil Daggers is what you might imagine a 3D bullet hell to be like, except in fps format. Initially if you are not familiar with fps games or are a bit lacking in hand eye coordination, you may feel like this game is quite difficult and just completely unfair, but only half of that is true. The difficulty from this game comes from not knowing what to expect and sometimes a lack of environment awareness, and this continues to be true throughout the game, as each section/wave of the game holding the same truth, primarily not knowing what new enemies do. The game has no direct story, but we can infer our character has the devil dagger and now must survive for all eternity, or at least until he dies from a mistake. Gameplay wise, it is quite simple but quite satisfying, especially when you see yourself passing your previous high score and avoiding the new enemies that spawned. One thing to note is that your hit box is quite smaller than most other fps games, so it does take a bit to get used to where you can actually be hit without going crazy, as one hit will kill you, so will falling off the map which is a fair size but can easily feel small in the heat of the moment. Long story short, its a simple game to pick up, but quite difficult to master. Your reaction time, environmental awareness, and patience will be tested. This is one of those games you keep around to come back to occasionally or just strongly dislike for being quite difficult to newbies and casual gamers. Verdict: 6/10 If you enjoyed this review, please follow our", "appid": "422970", "steamid": "profiles/76561198199595411", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "83", "votes_funny": "5", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1540382400.0}
