ame. There are sometimes bugs and freezes but its probably my fault for playing too long and overheating my computer. There's also that occasional what the ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• and where do I go type of vibe rarely every once and a while but I think its good and bad thing because the game doesn't hold your hand but it also makes you somethings look up tutorials and walkthroughs on how to get things done if you're completly confused.  There are also those weird bugs but I don't expect any game to be bugless and as of right now the bugs are quite harmless and not game breaking luckily. Overall I give this game a solid   Its fun, addicting, and you'll get hooked in the first couple hours of playing it. I recommend you buy it for the sake of supporting the wonderful devs and for you, the person reading this so you can play this yourself and enjoy it.", "appid": "435150", "steamid": "profiles/76561198102350967", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "20", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1514894400.0}
