{"text": "Thought the game to be lighthearted due to the look of it. The art is really colourful, therefore also quite deciving how serious this game is. A nice contrast to be fair, the cute art can amplify the heavy tone. How can something so harmless looking, be so dark, to the point that the chest feel heavy with torment? A rather pleasant suprise. The art strongest point, is the colouring and the characters designs, despite them being chibis. But they had odd porportions in the CG:s most of the time ..  The background are just blurried photos, not super distracting and they had a one to match each enviroment.  Same with the music, the game had a beffiting tune every moment! They were catchy, sad, spooky and one in paticular that I found so cosy <3. It's enough to make them stuck in my head, and make me want to start the game, just to listen to the music, due to the comfortable feeling it had at times. The writing was simple, easy to follow. And times it was really engaging! But also what the game need to improve the most ..It could be more variaton in wording things. Don't know how many times they said ''He seems to have a headache'' or ''Running his hand through his hair''.( Which is divided between the love interests. two with headache, and two hair runners.) The most annoying part with the writting was .. that the characters themselves had to say every aspect of their personality, especially the bad parts, and so does the MC, then they counter it .. As if you never will get to know the characters unless they tell you their characteristic descriptions .. which also got boring to read at times, making all the romance scenes super forced. There were also some typos, not many to be much of a distraction.  The story itself had .. a lot of sidetracking, to a point I was ''Wait .. which route am I on?'' Since the love interest seems to be hidden away a little with a lot of other things. Which could add a flavour to some routes, but also just be .. confusing.  Although, they did tie everything nicely together, and nothing leaves hanging, making it feel fullfilling to know all the routes.  All routes have a heavy topic, that involves the love interests, which was interesting. The love interests have a good dynamic between them, and rememberable personalites... till they butcher it with the writing, when they just say everything about themselves..Other than that, you can still get to know them. They could also angle one topic differenlty, which felt really refreshing, two different routes, two perspective. And something else important .. it's .. the game have a trustworthy skip-button <3 In the end, despite the writing of the characters, did I like this game. Espacially how heavy it could be, and dark, which what made this game good.  My favorit routes were Vally and Luca's. <3 And last, I bought this game .. since I liked Vally's design .. And I did indeed get what I wanted and more of this game. :D", "appid": "521540", "steamid": "profiles/76561198120498361", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "9", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1528718400.0}
