{"text": "\"Git gud.\" - Every Dark Souls player Dark Souls II: Scholar of the First Sin is a RPG difficult game created by From Software and published by Bandai Namco Games. Dark Souls II sets in Drangleic Castle and the plot is cryptic as usual. You play as customised class. The difference between Scholar of the First Sin and the vanilla Dark Souls II are the visual fidelity has been updated, rebalancing the items, some bosses from original Dark Souls II are absent and the items have been relocated. Also, the contents included all 3 DLCs The gameplay is still the same formula. The combat is great and responsive as usual. I was trying to move diagonally but the response time is terribly annoying. The multiplayer is the same formula, summoning your buddy with their White Soapstone and invading their world to kill noobs and say to them \"Git gud\". Shopkeepers are scattered all around the map, so you've got to remember where the shopkeepers are. The level design is amazing, especially the area like Black Gulch and Shrines of Amara can be the death fest. Speaking of death fest, you have to be cautious when wandering around the map because traps are everywhere. Keyboard and Mouse seems to be more responsive than the previous Dark Souls. The biggest plus is that you can customise the keyboard and mouse button layout. But there is only one limitation, the movement system seems to be clunky. To wrap this up, the great; combat system, level designs are cool yet brutal, replayability (New Game Plus) and responsive controls. The chaos; bosses from original Dark Souls II are missing, Crown of Ivory King and Sunken King DLCs aren't worth playable, Xbox button display when opening the door or reading the message with keyboard and mouse controls. The ugly; clunky movement system. The final score for this game is an 8 out of 10, better than average. This isn't the Dark Souls series you want to start. If you want to play Dark Souls II, grab the original or this game if you want to complete the Dark Souls collection.", "appid": "335300", "steamid": "profiles/76561198154393081", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1484395200.0}
