{"text": "At the moment Warframe is getting a mini-hype and actually is going into the steamcharts. And this game rly deserves this attention. The free to play system of Warframe is one of the fairest ones I`ve ever seen. U can pay real money for platinum (the real money currency) but u can actually trade it so you can get almost everything you want from the platinum shop by grinding and farming, many other games do this too but in most of these games you have to do and endless grind to get ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•. Compared to this Warframe also does this, but its not that hard. It`s mostly a Coop/Solo game. Its mostly about grinding and farming but its more rewarding in that category than other games. But playing a game just for farming, leveling and grinding is pretty poor tbh. If ur not a zombie who does that I can tell you that u still might have fun with Warframe due to the awesome and fast movement and combat. Another part that makes this game one of my favs is the community. Its hard to find a gamecommunity like the one of Warframe. Ok U`ll find ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• everywhere but U`ll hardly see some in Warframe. When u got a question at the beginning (tust me U`ll have many questions!!!) u can just ask the global chat. There are always players who`ll help u or maybe even carry you. I was afraid that with getting hyped the community will become worse, cause the mainstream might start playing this game. I`m glad that this didn`t happened. The communtiy still grows but is still as awesome as it used to be, lets just hope it will stay this way! My last point would be the longtime motivation. I played it for 368 hours at this point and there is still so much content and new game mechanics I still didn`t discovered. Even players with 1000+ hours told me that its still this way after 1000 hours. At the beginning of this game its hard to get in and find motivation, I also had to start several times to get hooked by it. It takes a bit but its so worth it. Like I said, if u have questions ask other players or use the wiki of this game. At first its annoying but after a while U`ll always get exited about learning more game aspects. The best start in this game u can have is knowing someone who got much experience in Warframe who can lead you through the hard start. Have fun! And sorry if I made typos or any grammar mistakes.", "appid": "230410", "steamid": "profiles/76561198071608867", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1510056000.0}
