{"text": "I was a beta tester, so I got a free key.  ^^  is a visual novel developed by Catnip and published by Catnip and Kikai Digital.  You take on the role of Shi Mo, a student who has recently transferred from No. 1 to No.2 High School.  There are rumors surrounding what happened to Shi Mo at his previous school and thus, the reason for his transfer.  As a result, students avoid and fear him.  On his first day at his new school, he meets Ran Xiaoyu, a quiet, sensitive girl.  He quickly discovers that she is being bullied and thus, she avoids her classmates as much as possible.  The two of them quickly form a bond, but I'll end my story synopsis here to avoid spoilers. I'll move onto the gameplay briefly.  As this is a visual novel with choices, the choices you make determine what ending you get.  There are 3 different endings and 2 choices presented.  Also, there are a fair number of CGs as well as a varied soundtrack and a number of Steam achievements.  That's pretty much it in regards to gameplay.  XD As I've gone over the story and gameplay, I'll move onto my critique.    deals with the serious topic of high school bullying, which piqued my interest.  I'm sure that almost everyone has been victims of high school bullying or has witnessed it, so I feel like this subject is relatable.  The story deals with a serious topic, but there are light-hearted moments as well.  I liked how the relationship between Shi Mo and Ran develops, especially if you choose to go for the happy (true) ending.  Ran's character is Chinese voice acted, which I felt was a nice change from the visual novels that have Japanese and/or English voice acting.  In regards to writing, I felt that the story was very well-paced.  Overall, it is on the short side but it delivers its message effectively, and I liked how, depending on the choices made, there are different ways of dealing with bullying and how those decisions affect others.  The art is beautiful to view and it's in an anime style.  I really liked viewing the CGs especially.  The soundtrack has a fair number of tracks and each one captured the scene and mood it was placed in well. Overall, I'd recommend   for anyone who likes visual novels and wants to enjoy a good story.  It is on the short side but still, it's very enjoyable for the content you get.  It's worth the price point and it delivers on its message.  It took me just a little over 3 hours to 100% complete the game and get all of the achievements.  (I did skip over text I already read, so bear that in mind.)  As the game is under \"Steam is learning about this game,\" achievements won't count towards your overall global total until it achieves enough sales and/or reviews.  However, it's totally worth getting and being a fan of visual novels, I really enjoyed  .  ^^", "appid": "1238520", "steamid": "profiles/76561198128704797", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "31", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1595332800.0}
