{"text": "its a great game, The graphics look amazing (also a range of lower less nice looking settings for all you potato gamers)  There are two main modes, arcade and realistic; in arcade you move faster, get respawns and a map that shows enemy positions. good for quick easy games without having to put much thought into it. Realistic modes are well, more realistic. you will have to rely on skill and your senses for this one, very rewarding mode. (there is also simulator but thats a whole other review in itself) One downside to this game is its grind. There are currently 7 nations in war thunder, each with long tech trees containing tanks and planes (and currently 4 countries with naval tech trees) These trees range from tiers 1 to 6 with each tier needing more xp to unlock new vehicals.  This system is good as it keeps newer players with less experience away from higher tier battles until they gain enough required expirence to unlock the higher tier vehicals.  another issue is balancing, while you dont have to worry about an supersonic jet gunning down your early war bi-planes. due to stronger vehicals having their own tiers of gameplay. but even being matched into a game with tanks around the same level as yours, you will encounter some unbalanced things, but its kind of fitting as war isnt a fair game. This game is great fun with friends, and offers hours of gameplay with different playstyles and gamemodes depending on if you like to fly fast nimble fighters that can shoot down other players, or large strategic bombers to destroy enemy bases, ranging down to slow firing but one shot kill tank destroyers or quick rapid firing cannons and machine guns.  7/7, would recommend you give this game a try, even more so that it is free. (but keep in mind that higher tiers can be unlocked faster by spending money)", "appid": "236390", "steamid": "profiles/76561198108182613", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1547035