{"text": "It's hard to say for now because I haven't played or reached the \"end game\" but so far the game is promising, the story is interesting and the cinematics is just amazing. I do enjoy the lore and the whole story part, combat is also amazing, You can choose three classes and you are not forced to have one main character, you can play all three classes or play one class, you have the freedom to do it. Personally, Warlock is the best for me I enjoy the flexibility of the class from the heals to the massive damage.  The weapon and armor details are one thing that made me play this game, most are well made and look aesthetic with different designs.  So far best things for the game for me are the looks and the story, I am sure later on in the game I will find more stuff that I like but for the first impression is something that I would invest my time in it.  That's for the pros, but every game has its cons. Cons for this game I would say is that for a new player (like me) trows you in this big content-wise game with so little explanation on what is happening and who are you, as for me that I enjoy games with a story. It was a little turn-off but it's not a game-breaker, I wish there can be a guide or something for new players to know which story to play first to follow the order of the storyline.  So far a good story, a lot of activities to do alone, public or with friends.  Amazing weapons and armor designs and skins to ships, lack of a new player guide. 9/10", "appid": "1085660", "steamid": "profiles/76561198022480428", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1573473600.0}
