{"text": "First of all, I'm not into games like these, they aren't really what I like to play and enjoy. I'll start with the art, it's very nice, haven't played that much, but I can clearly see that there was a lot of work put into this game to make it look as it is. I was surprised as to how well the game looked when it was raining in the world. They made it so that the rain drops are sliding through your screen, while that may not be so uncommon it certainly looks beautiful and added to the enjoyment. 10/10  Story, well as I only have 1 hour logged right now, I can't say much cause I've only did like 3 missions, but it doesn't look bad so far. Music is fitting, sounds are good too, I could constantly hear monsters so I kept thinking that someone is close while there was actually noone :D.  Gameplay, well I'm not sure if this is how this type of games should be played, but it certainly feels like so. Combat feels nice, skills too, only tried the shadow class so far. At first it looks like it's very easy, but even fighting with pistol isn't that easy once you're surrounded by a lot of enemies and have no space to dash to. There is also blocking, well I didn't play with sword much, so I can't comment, but when I tried I wasn't sure how to use it effectively. As you progress through the game, more different enemies appear. Price of this game is only 10 euro where as other games from greenlight cost much more and aren't even close to being as polished or having as much content as this game does. I personally wouldn't buy it, BUT ONLY BECAUSE THIS ISN'T WHAT I LIKE. Overall even though I don't find this type of games fun, I did enjoy playing it and thus people who like games like these should really have fun.", "appid": "612670", "steamid": "profiles/76561198024527360", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "9", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1492084800.0}
