{"text": "In 2008 I played the flash version of this game on Kongregate, and I loved it, even the humor was rich back then. My friend pedro Triple B captures all of that. Shooting in slow motion never gets old in any game (Which wasn't that great when Max Payne did it actually.) with the addition of split shooting which works so fantasticly well that it puts Devil May Cry to shame. The first and second chapters are the most intense, in which you actually have to rock your brains to keep the momentum going by keeping the combo score alive if you want to achieve more points and actually unlock all of the Achievements. There are several unique levels that are truly not only engaging but hilarious. However, not every game is perfect, not even when you're being hostile taked over by a banana. Later on you have platform levels, and while they aren't really that bad and you can go through them like a walk in the park it brings the shooting and action to a sudden stop, as if out of nowhere you're slamming the brakes with your eye sockets. It kills it for me, the platform levels that HAVE enemies are awesome and can be unforgiving, but a game in which at it's core is nothing but shooting and then out of nowhere you're not allowed to shoot anymore. Imagine if Hotline Miami had a mandatory stealth lev- err I mean imagine if you were playing DOOM 2016 and you had to stop the glory kills to instead have a tea party with the demons. My second and last pet peeve is the fact that the game feels like it's lacking so much. Not in terms of levels mind you, 51 levels is a bloody a lot even though you can finish them all in 2 hours, but for a game like this it lacks the prior Arena mode or an arcade mode like that. I can DEFINITELY see this game get supported by steam workshop and people implanting their own levels with their own dialogues and make the game just as hilarious. All in all, I recommend My Friend Pedro Blowjobs Boobies and Bellends but only if you can swiftly ignore the platform section, since once you finish the game you can just handpick the level you want and kill baddies at your leisure", "appid": "557340", "steamid": "profiles/76561198045598071", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561291200.0}
