{"text": "It's a hard decision to actually recommend this game because there are a lot of things that they can't seem to fix, the basics of it are really great, however it fails when it comes to it's community which is very toxic and sabotaging the competitive aspect of the game many times. Pros: + Tactical gameplay + Wide amount of operators with different abilities + Nice maps that have a realistic vibe and allow tactical gameplay + Keeps getting updated with new operators and maps + Teamplay is key (And with that we come to the cons) Cons: - Since this game relies on teamplay, it only needs 1-2 egotistic or ignorant players in your team to ruin a match - Ubisoft servers can have problems at times that prevent you from connecting, maintenance happens more often than in other games and it can take hours - Toxic community (The worst problem of this game): It feels like every 2nd-3rd match there will be a griefer who will do anything to ruin a match, they will friendly fire but not kill you so the system can't catch up on them, they ruin your equipment or do anything else that ruins a match but won't get them into any trouble. These are most likely people who have a real life that sucks bad and they get a sense of control when they ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• up competitive online matches because that's their only way of getting attention and feeling superior. There are a lot of angry and insultive players who will insult you for no reason and blame everything on you if a round fails, even though they died right at the beginning. There are also a lot of idiots who refuse to teach new players and instead just insult them.  Not even in ranked matches you are safe, so be prepared to waste a good amount of time and ranks because of griefers since you can't leave a match without receiving a penalty (up to 23+ hours) and it doesn't matter if you lose a match because some griefers ruined it.  Most of the time votekick will be used to kick players who take too long to load but it almost never gets used to kick griefers, so don't rely on that", "appid": "359550", "steamid": "profiles/76561197977159343", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1584014400.0}
