{"text": "Witcher 3 is the best game I've ever played, let me tell you why. Story: Witcher 3's story gives you a huge overlook on the world, you meet so many interesting characters on the way and the story is really long, but don't worry, there is a lot of side content which dosen't make the main quests dragged out. Characters: I f***ing love Geralt, he is so enjoyable to listen too and his realationships with other characters further increase this, the other side characters are awesome too and get so much development. Setting: Velen, Novigrad and Skellige are so variant and nice, and all of the continents are massive with alot of content like missions, contracts, character interaction, laws, etc, and Witcher 3 is probably one of the best looking games ever, the graphics hold up to games in 2018. Gameplay: The fighting is great, it feels immersive and there are so many diffrent powers you can use to your adventage. Villans/Enemies: The Wild Hunt are menacing, each time they show up you are like ''oh f**k'' and there are alot of creatures and diffrent monsters, and you have a beastiarity so you can read about new monsters you meet, It's awesome. Upsides: great story looks beautiful plays well you care for the characters good villans/enemies lots of stuff to do downsides: fall damage is too high sometimes the map can be confusing they use the same character models ALOT can be alot of glitches (but it's to be expected from such a huge game) need an ''okay'' PC to play", "appid": "292030", "steamid": "profiles/76561198070779774", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1526126400.0}
