{"text": "Kudos to Bethesda and their shamelessness to charge you full price for F4 VR while you already own the original non-vr game. That being said I still bought the game to experience the first big AAA game in VR. Unfortunately it's disappointing in many ways. At this point I should note that Iam a big VR fan when it comes to other VR games. My major criticism is that the immersion of F4 VR (Skyrim VR aswell) is worse than in almost every other VR game. I cannot pinpoint a reason for that but the immersion in other VR games can be breathtaking while in this game the environment feels \"flat\" although Iam playing with the best VR and pc gaming has to offer right now (Vive Pro and max settings). Close objects can feel pretty real but the world around it not so much. Furthermore you are not able to really interact with anything (opening doors like you would in rl, picking things up, grabbing them and so on. It's always just pointing at items and clicking a button on your vive controller. That takes away even more of the immersion. In conclusion it can be said that I don't believe in this type of vr games. Playing something that is made for VR from the start is MUCH MUCH more fun.", "appid": "611660", "steamid": "profiles/76561198168423186", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": "21", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1530360000.0}
