{"text": "There's apparently some controversy with the creater of the game, but being as how this is a review of the game, it really shouldn't be mentioned. I'm only bringing it up so that you, the reader, are aware that I will not be bringing it up. I expected myself to be drawn in to the game with a name like that. I expected it to be compelling, immersive and whatnot. Hey, you might convince someone that it's immersive if you use noise canceling headphones with the music and had extremely moody lighting. And at that point, if you're going to go that far to get into the flow of a game, don't pick this one. There is no flow. You don't have to think about your decisisions if you want to get the \"best\" ending. Always pick the topmost answer. Want to get the worst ending? Pick the bottom answer. I suppose there is one good thing about this game though. It's very linear and easy to follow. It's like tetris, simple and quick, but certainly not as entertaining or addicting. Certainly doesn't have as good a soundtrack.  I wasted my money on this game. \"How could you waste money on a game that's free?\" Simple, time is money. Just do yourself a favor and skip over this game. 1/10 wouldn't like this game even if it came with free sexual favors.", "appid": "270170", "steamid": "profiles/76561198046817164", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1408622400.0}
