{"text": "Review on : oculus rift s Okey, the concept of the game is brilliant ... I always liked Mirror's Edge concept games but.... There are way too many game breaking bugs that I can't tolerate. Jumping works 80% time ,Im using the A button and not works , leads to falling off while running to edges . Grabbing panels seems easy to catch , yet it bugs out many many times that I can't climb up . Pistol grabbing and reloading are the worst things of all... there are only a bit of a hitbox where the game lets you do these things. Endless mode is nothing like randomly generated map , there are too many places that repeated for that 5 run that I went. I know these can be fixed ( early access ) but at this point , I can't recommend anyone this game yet.", "appid": "1292040", "steamid": "profiles/76561198018372654", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1599307200.0}
{"text": "After almost an entire year of playing this game, I have to say I quit. For a few reasons -The Design of the Game. The game looks incredibly beautiful, but not only is it not well optimized the net code also happens to be extremely horrible.  -The Classes and the overall gameplay design. What's good about an MMO with only DPS and some light healers? Who's to gain agro and whatnot? In Black Desert, almost if not all the classes are developed to play like a dps, with exception of some mages who have healing skills. -The Pearl Shop. Some items such as pet food, pets, clothing, are all acceptable items for a mmo, but Black Desert overprices all of it. Want a outfit for your character? Congratlutations, you've now paid over 20 dollars for an armor set that would be locked to that one single character. Damn, even though Final Fantasy prices outfit at this price at least they have frequent sales. -The PVP system. I don't really criticize this point, in fact I love the PVP system. They allow you to flag others at the cost of Karma, which could make you a target of ingame guards when the number hits zero. Sounds great doesn't it? But what happens when a group of friends flag people consistently because they accidentally entered their farming areas? It doesn't end well. Higher level farming areas are generally filled with these groups, making it impossible for solo players or people in general to level up at the end game areas.", "appid": "582660", "steamid": "profiles/76561198176228589", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1519646400.0}
