{"text": "I've said it before and I'll say it again. This game becomes a mind-numbing spam-fest where everyone just spams their one or two strong combos that are hard or near impossible to counter, because regular attacks will only get you parried and punished hard. Spamming's all that's left to do besides parrying. The most successful duelers do nothing. They just wait until you attack them, then parry and punish you. If you feint they just cancel too, turning the game into a pointless \"whoever attacks, loses\". It is a prime example of poorly thought out mechanics and balancing. Repeating the same attacks / combos should increase the stamina drain proportionally. End of story. The dude spams it once, twice, thrice, stamina depleted, counter-attacks incoming. The fact that you can spam 5 - 7 times the same things without any drawback at all is absurd. The story couldn't be more uninteresting. The characters interact with each other as if they're in a sitcom. In fact, the only thing seperating the cutscenes and an unfunny sitcom is the laugh track. This game is the least optimized game since Homefront: The Revolution. The graphics are alright for a modern game. The community is close to non existent at this point, the only game mode being played is 1v1 duel. The leveling system is an unending grind (no $hit, this is a Ubisoft game). There are 60 prestige levels and you are required to get up to level 20 to upgrade to prestige levels, that equals to 1200 levels. Of course, there's a lootbox system included (again, Ubisoft),and the gear you obtain from them improves your character statistics. If you're looking for a \"war\" game, buy Chivalry: Medieval Warfare, not this steaming pile of crap.", "appid": "304390", "steamid": "profiles/76561198309745321", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "28", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1537099200.0}
