{"text": "The idea for Cannibal Crossing is pretty forthcoming: another zombie apocalypse scavenge-and-base-building survival game. The reality of it, at present, is that its generally good \"game feel\" is buried underneath an unholy mire of bugginess. In the first hour of play I experienced the following: And presumably not a bug (although I honestly can't be sure!), but a point of criticism:   I don't care if it needs to be a skill, a pickup, filled out as you explore the map, whatever, but   is a repeating tileset of asphalt and dirt roads, trees, stumps, and the same handful of buildings repeated over and over which shuffles each time you die. It's impossible to keep your bearings for any real length of time. It's by the team who've made Death Road to Canada the rousing success that it is so I have reasonable faith in them, but for the time being I would not under any circumstances recommend this based on my experiences and say maybe go check out Cataclysm: DDA if you wouldn't mind a game like this in a more traditional turn-based roguelike wrapper.", "appid": "1304090", "steamid": "profiles/76561197979724838", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1604923200.0}
