{"text": "Missing features. Incorrect coding of critical components. Game breaking bugs. Simple grammar errors are rampant. Would have gotten a refund if I hadnt played for too long before realising my mistake. If these things are patched out/fixed, then I will change my mind. Edit: A few of the things I've noticed that are wrong; There are many issues with race traits and abilities. Xenophobic has no use. I've looked in the game files, and I see what its intended to do, but when in game it gives no bonuses at all. It is the same with the base production bonus from wealthy. With tourism moved to the diplomatic ability, the trait that gives bonuses and penalties to tourism becomes moot, and an abusable source of trait points for race creation. The advanced morale improvements are also locked behind the diplomatic ability, thus making it a neccesity in race creation. The now 'vanilla' morale improvements are substandard. With the \"Easy to Please\" specialisation giving 4 base morale to all panets (worth 2 'vanilla' morale improvements) being restricted to the diplomatic ability, not selecting the ability is purposely crippling a race. Taking the Diplomatic ability also makes the Hopeful ability redundant, as the diplomatic ability is able to provide much more than 1 morale. The Handy trait provides a 15% reduction in ship maintence for one trait point, and a 20% reduction for two trait points. This doesnt fit with the progression of the other traits, which is often x%/2x% bonuses or penalties, making the 20% selection (a 5% increase) wasteful. The time travelers ability has the description \"Great tech, no infrastructure.\". This is misleading, as all starting races have no infrastructure either, and there are no penalties that the time traveler trait gives that would fit such a description. It is simply free high level technology. This also devalues the Intuitive ability, as the 50 researh points granted are worth one early game tech, compared to three mid to late game technologies. Each of these techs provide imediate benefits, where as the singular early game techonlogy may not be of use until the buildings/components unlocked by it are able to be built once the starting critical improvements are completed. The Vigilant ability is shown twice in the race editor, and the Zealots ability defined in the game files is not displayed at all. You can no longer engage in diplomacy with minor races. At all. None. Its just gone. ALL weapons beyond first tier require resources. And these requirements seem to follow no progression, eg the experimental antimatter missile has a cost of 2 antimatter for 2 missile attack, where the Harpoon, which is given in the same tech, gives 4 missile attack for 1 antimatter. The protoype durantium driver costs 12 durantium and 1 thulium. That is significantly higher than any other weapon resource cost, especially when the Pulse cannon -w hich is provided in the same tech - has a cost of only 1 thulium. The farming buildings make no sense. The second farm tech gives access to two farm improvements, one improvement costs 1 elerium, 1 monotasium, gives 3 food, and has 0.5 maintenece. The other improvement has no resource cost, no maintenece, and also gives 3 food. Clearly, the farm with no resource cost or maintenence is the best choice, so why give the other one at all, when it provides no extra benefit? This continues further down the farming tech path, with the third farming tech unlocking two farm improvements, one that cost 2 elerium, 2 monotasium, gives 4 food, and has a maitenence of 0.8. The other farm improvement unlocked costs 1 monotasium, also gives 4 food, and has no maintenece. Again, a clear superior. It is also worth mentioning that monotasium is very rare, it can only be acquired if present on a planet, at a mining rate of 0.1/0.2/0.3 per turn with requisite techs. All of the projects (research project, military subsidies, birth subsisdies, morale allowance, cultural festival) are now gone, despite still being present in the tech tree. Many building listed in the tech tree do not show in the construction tree, eg the research coordination centre. The information displayed when you hover over your treasury has no proctical use. It shows the average income of your planets, the highest producer and the highest spender. It does not show your net income, despite saying 'net income' when hovered over. This means you must constanly open the govern tab to check your actual income. The diplomat citizen cannot be reassigned in sent to a planet. The Rankings in the Summary tab of the upper right HUD does not follow the rankings shown in the diplomacy menu. Devs haave said that the ai can rush purchase without having the amount being deducted from their treasury. Free money/colonies/buildings.   (look at the second comment). I will post more as I find them.", "appid": "527070", "steamid": "profiles/76561198072638400", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1494158400.0}
