{"text": "First of all let me say that this is the kind of game I was looking for some time now, and I really want to like it. That being said, it is not a finished product and it has some problems.  First major problem is that the player base is not nearly big enough. IMO expanding the player base should be one of the developer's priorities, and you won't succeed at that by focusing on Pro Membership features like the latest Manager Skills update. Also if you want players to keep coming back after trying the game offer them the possibility to make the club their own (like let them at least choose the badge shape and colors from some presets while Pro Members can upload any badge). One more thing that could help ‚Äî a basic tutorial or better yet in-game tooltips (online help outside of the game itself isn't really the best way to handle this). I agree that some things should be behind the paywall but you have to offer something to F2P players (and not make a mistake of going P2W), it has to be well-balanced because who will be crazy enough to buy Pro Membership in a dead game?  Second problem is the match engine which isn't great and players tend to do some senseless things like passing the ball back when they have a clean path towards the opposition's goal. Hopefully they are still improving the engine.  Third major problem is the way the calendar/fixtures work (requesting for matches, managers have to be online) and that is especially highlighted with the lack of active players. I would prefer that the matches have fixed time, if you can get online and attend the match great, if not offer some basic tactical instructions that will be preset and played out even if the player is offline (something like old school browser online managers like  .  TL;DR I'm recommending this game because it has a lot of potential and it is F2P so it really doesn't cost you anything to try it, besides I don't think there's anything like it right now on the market (something between Football Manager and Hattrick). If this was a finished product I wouldn't recommend it, but hopefully it can still improve. Maybe my recommendation will change in the future if there's no improvement... EDIT: After spending additional 40 hours on the game and researching some of the past updates I can't really recommend it anymore. This is a basic football manager game (no direct transfers between teams, no stadiums, staff removed - I haven't experienced it but it's replaced with pay only feature \"manager skills\", youth teams - pay only feature, one match instruction per player, lacking match engine, P2W team boost etc.) that you have to pay almost ‚Ç¨80 PER YEAR to be competitive in all while the player base is tiny and most paying players have more than one active team... So much potential yet, in my opinion, the development is going in the wrong direction. I would be pleasantly surprised if they manage to turn this wreck around and turn in into a good game that new players would want to try, continue playing, and support financially...", "appid": "468070", "steamid": "profiles/76561198051867376", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1589716800.0}
