{"text": "After 1400 hours of gameplay I can say that this game really deserves serious fixes.It is a good game, but the toxic community and incompetent devs ruin it all, also this is my first serious review that I write on a game.        First of all, I know it's not easy to make a game, but first launch your updates in PTB like you did in the past updates, to make sure that everything is working fine, and nothing is broken.You need to take more  serious the situation of the bug fixes rather than releases of DLC.I bought every single DLC, to find after 1 week after the release - the killer is nerfed to the ground and unplayable in higher ranks.You need to understand that the main focus of skill is in the mid-ranks-to high-ranks not in low-ranks, stop nerfing the killers/survivors perks/actions speed at the n00b's opinion, it's foolish.       Second of all, I've never seen a toxic community such as DBD's community,the main toxic group of people comes from survivor, with their behaviour of body-blocking, tea-bagging, mocking the killer, Dead Hard, Borrowed Time, heals in front of the killer,  etc, that can infuriate the player.Of course, the toxic can come from the killer too, tunneling, facecamping(it has been fixed, GG DEVS), blocking in corners, taking the game hostage( both sides of the game can do this),etc.And one more serious problem is the incorrect desing of \"The Hatch\", as a killer it forces you to stare at a survivor for hours until he/she makes the escape action in order to grab him/her, and as an average survivor you keep starring at the killer 'till he gets bored to take a hit in order to escape(trying to lose the killer, or completing the gens being an alternate route of escape).        As a final thought, if you don't let the toxic community to get to you, getting over the  frustrating game-breaking bugs, and enjoy the overall point of the game without getting mad, then I recommend this game, otherwise I can't.     I will leave a negative review 'till the major bugs are being fixed.", "appid": "381210", "steamid": "profiles/76561198223494928", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1479816000.0}
