{"text": "Honestly even if it's free game i wouldn't recommend it. It's really plenty of similar games but this one is just trying to take what's best from shooters like quake, warsow (warfork) and unreal tournament (the first one), and it's not the greatest rip off which i ever seen. Graphic looks like it stops at early 2k but thats not bad in terms of performance and gameplay. Menu is not very intuitive and there is plenty things which you will have to modify by command line to get best experience (same like it used to be in quake) - on plus - lots of commands are explained in console what they are for (when you start typing them) - so you can find some usefull ones just by spending time with console.  The main thing which i did not like was ammo indication next to crosshair also dash moves are slightly odd, can't feel them like in warsow for example. There is a few other similar titles which will prowide u better experience on shooter arena like for example: Quake Live, Unreal Tournament or Warfork - all of those got better graphic and gameplay will not feel so bad, the only difference will be that all of titles which i mention above got high entry level, so for people not familiar with FPS games gonna have hell from start on most of the servers.", "appid": "967460", "steamid": "profiles/76561198796717601", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "11", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1577793600.0}
