{"text": "For me RAGE 2 is a MIXED of really GOOD and really BAD. First of all this is not a game about the story, but it's made for people that really like shooting and blowing up things in the most fun and absurd way! Overall i can say i liked the game but unfortunately i can't reccomend it at full price, i would say it's worth around 20-30‚Ç¨. PROS: - The world design is wonderful expecially in it's unique lighting effects and colors (for some people it could look too blurry and if you want the game to look more \"sharper\" i suggest you to turn off in the graphic options \"Depth of Field\",\"Chromatic Aberration\" and, if you want it to look even more sharper, set the ANTI-ALIASING to \"FXAA\"); - The Gunplay and Combat in itself it's just AMAZING, with 8 different weapons (if you have the standard edition) with INCREDIBLE design and uniqueness, olso the abilities are WONDERFUL and so satisfying to use; - There are some really cool boss fights, expecially during the main missions of the story, and also really fun convoy encounters. CONS: - The Story, which is the best part of the game, it's unfortunately too short and can be finished in 10 hours or even less (it follows the pattern of Mad Max's story which can be a let down for some people); - The camps feel pretty good to complete but the OPEN WORLD in itself it's lifeless and in some parts of the map it feels hollow; - The driving feels really bad with almost all the vehicles which can ruin the fun convoy encounters; - There are bugs and glitches during the playthrough, some of whitch can stop you from continuing as intended; - All the enemies are too easy to fight (i played on hard without upgrading any health or defense) and because of that it can feel boring at times even with it's incredibly fun combat; - One boss fight is re-used like 5 times and, despite the first time being somewhat fun, it's also too easy and you feel no accomplishment in beating it; PERSONAL THOUGHTS: For me this game needs really bad a NEW GAME + mode, expecially because there is a roadmap of free content started this month and continuing in the later months which feels really useless for people like me that already played and completed the game at 100%. This would be a nice addition to the game that for sure would keep me playing it. Also there is paid content coming which is shameful giving the fact that this game has not much of it from the start, it would be worth 60‚Ç¨ all in one and not spread between pre-order, deluxe edition and DLC's!", "appid": "548570", "steamid": "profiles/76561198118692497", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "39", "votes_funny": "9", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1558699200.0}
