{"text": "This actually didn't work for me sadly.  Even on my Low End PC.  I lost FPS in CSGO.  I saw people were getting steam cards for reviewing though so I'll do a honest reveiw. So I started my day as usual.  Gay as ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•.  Ready to game.  I had my birthday party last night so I was Hungover but still lit.  So I looked at sales and saw this CPUcores.  \"‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• I thought to myself\"  By the same TIm guy that made all the other ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• for me that didn't work.  Might as well buy!  Couldn't be a scam at all.  (even though all the reviews were great it seemed kind of fishy.)  But I downloaded it anyway. I downloaded it and I acutally lost FPS in CSGO.  A CPU oriented game.  That makes no sense.  This Unparks your cores?  But it didn't work.  And it also said I only have 1 core when I infact have 2.  ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•.  Okay.  I still refunded even if I was wrong. Now I would like to talk about some of the reviews going around on this.  I think they are all lies.  They look fishey and after doing research on this it seems like it didn't help at all (And there are other programs that work so much better than this that actually work correctly for free!!!!)  Then I saw that a guy got 3 FREE STEAM CARDS when he didn't even have the software installed?  Where's my free steam cards?  I was lead on.  This didn't work at all for me.  I want some cards.  IT WAS MY BIRTHDAY TIM WHERE IS MY PRESENT. *cough cough*.  I know my computer is already ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•.  I know.  I am running on a GT 710 2 GB with a A4-6030 3.70 GhZ DUAL CORE.  Which the application identified as a single core which makes no sense. Dear Tim, Please stop leading people on.   I love you buddy.  But this doesn't work and the people that say it does seem like they have been paid to do so.  Which I do not appreciate.  On Fourms they say you are a scammer.  Maybe you aren't a scammer but a ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• developer.  Sorry man.  But this is a no from me. From, A man who you gave a dream just to crush.\\ I would like to add a conversation that me and him had.  After the last time I responded he stopped responding to me completley (Read bottom to Top) ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•'s |   Just now   Where'd you go Tim? I need awnsers?   ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•'s |   52 minutes ago    - Something else you have made that is a scam?  Would also like to post this. And state that I think you or somebody deleted a post about him getting three free steam cards. I still have the guys profile and will be sure to ask him about why he got the cards and how he got them. I just want anwsers not your trying to tell me you are a tiny developer. This is people money not a game. (Sorry if I sound rude. Just kinda mad after reading all this ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• about your other programs that you have created being scams.)   StartupTim  [developer] 1 hour ago   I'm afraid I don't give things for free just for review. As a gamer myself, I appreciate when reviews don't come with a cost of getting free things :)  As a developer, especially a tiny developer, reviews are really important to me. Negative reviews especially hurt us. This is a big reason why I try very hard to help everybody out, even if it doesn't work well for them, so they have a positive experience.  But that being said, I still wouldn't give something free just for a review.  Instead, I hope people judge things by the merits of the program, the game, and the developer, and if their experience was overall a positive one. I hope you can understand :) Cheers!!     ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•'s |   1 hour ago   But Tim. What about my free steam cards? Or if you buy me the thing again sure. I will gladly try it out again.   StartupTim  [developer] 1 hour ago   Sorry you sold some Skins and it didn't work out as you wanted. But I have to say that following the steps mentioned should really help. Also testing using FRAPs is a big key to seeing results, not only in FPS raising, but in FPS minimums. I read/respond to every review as I truly want people to have a POSITIVE experience. Even if the software isn't a fit for them, I want them to feel like they are respected and valued and feel a bit more positive for having tried the software out. I encourage people to try things out and refund if it isn't a good fit. My goal is to make gaming more fun after not, not be greedy and gobble up all the dollars, and I overall just want to make a positive impact on gamers.   ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•'s |   1 hour ago   Nah Tim. Already refunded. Some Steam Cards though yeah sure I'll give it another try XD. It'll be my bday present Tim. I sold a skin for this and I was very unhappy </3 StartupTim  [developer] 1 hour ago   Hello ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•! > \"And it also said I only have 1 core when I infact have 2\" Are you sure you don't actually have 1 core but hyper-threading enabled? Try running this command on your pc from a command prompt: wmic cpu get name, NumberOfCores, NumberOfLogicalProcessors /Format:List This will show how many FULL, REAL cores you have, and how many virtual/non-full cores you have. For example, AMD Bulldozers have 2 core modules, whereas the module has 1 REAL core and 1 SHARED core (aka non-full core). I suggest going to   and using those settings BUT making this tweak: Then go to CPUCores -> Advanced -> Constrain Web Browsers and enable that. UNSELECT the \"Isolate OS\" option and \"Game on dedicated\" option.  I hope you can take a peek at the settings and see if things can work and then hopefully feel positive enough to take that into account for your review. Happy gaming and I wish you well :)", "appid": "384300", "steamid": "profiles/76561198144105531", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "25", "votes_funny": "4", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1497268800.0}
