{"text": "tyfus spel", "appid": "578080", "steamid": "profiles/76561197990560829", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "10", "votes_funny": "5", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1515499200.0}
{"text": "I am done with this game and the cancerous playerbase. So, so done. No videogame should ever cause this much grief, anxiety and stress.  Firstly, I won't even get into the disgusting reputation the developers have created for themselves, of their own doing. All you have to do is read another 2 or 3 reviews on this game to get a detailed fill-in on all of that noise. So I'll skip it, because at this point, we're all just beating a dead horse. Nothing is going to change.  Unfortunately I can't recommend this game right now. The only thing keeping it alive at the moment is the community-run servers, which are absolute cancer. I've been banned from two of the most popular ones within a week, without so much as a explanation (yes I installed Discord specifically to read the rules of both prior to playing, and as far as I know, I broke zero rules).  As I said, the community is a joke, filled with moderator-boot-lickers and sore losers. Which is sad when it's the only thing keeping this game above water right now. Speaks volumes of the game itself.  The community-run servers are hardly a fun time, filled with fun-police moderators and people sucking up to them. Do one thing wrong (where the term 'wrong' is a matter of opinion) and you'll have 10+ people whinging to the moderators over discord and BAM; you're permabanned with zero explanation and zero chance to put your own side of the story across.  The official servers are better, but not by much. The chance for permaban is completely non-existant, which is actually a bad thing. Apex packs of what the community fondly calls \"Chinese Hackers\" fill these official servers, making them virtually unplayable for longer amounts of time.  These \"Chinese Hackers\" (not really hackers, just Chinese players with insane amounts of time on their hands) will kill anyone and anything on sight and they span the map in huge groups of apex predators. If you happen to fight one and win, they simply ALT+F4 and exit the game, only to spawn back in as another apex with another of their many accounts, and wreck you while you are weak from the fight.  Not only does this mean you die, but also means that both of the apex's they used to kill you survived. This makes them virtually unkillable and they are LITERALLY ruining the game. If they get wind of anyone else creating a pack that could take them on, they appear out of nowhere and kill everyone. They are hilariously and infuriatingly coordinated and will often leave you wondering how they even knew where you were and how many they'd need to squash you out.  I stopped playing for nearly 2 months solely because of these Chinese apex groups. Haven't heard a word from the devs via steam for months now, nor have there been any updates. Constant YouTube videos about \"plans\" that have been \"coming soon\" for months, some even years.  The game is beautiful, but unfortunately that's about as far as the compliments go. There are so many issues that haven't been fixed for way too long now. If you bought this game within the last 2 months, no one could blame you for thinking it was a dead game. I gave The Isle 200 hours (nothing compared to the 1,000+ game hours of some of the other negative reviews here) before I got sick enough to write my FIRST review on steam, and it's a negative one. That, if nothing else, should tell you something about this game, and the fact that it is consistently going downhill. EDIT: GIANT UPDATE In light of the huge update in the past few weeks, some new issues have arrised. Apart from promising fixes for certain issues (like punishing combat logging, which they stated they'd fixed in the patch notes but simply.. didn't - not sure what the go is there) and then not actually fixing them, the new Thenyaw map is a nice change. A little hard to traverse, with far too few flat surfaces and 90% of the map seemingly made up of mountains and stupidly steep hills and far too many trees, making it impossible to see where you are going as soon as you are anything larger than a Utahraptor. Impossible spawn points (spawning so far away at the A$$-end of the map that you literally starve to death before even encountering anyone else if you're a carnivore, and some spawn points not even having vegetation around for herbivores. Twice in a row I starved to death as a herbivore while trying to make it to my friends on the other side of the map, and I was actively looking for shrubs to eat the entire way there. And yes, I knew what to look for) and OP spawn points, where you can camp as a herbivore - in a discreet and quiet corner of the map with water and food mere metres from one another - until you're fully grown.  V3 is utter garbage. Other than these things, it's a nice map. Looks great, nice long views, some decent hangout spots... But not enough landmarks. I learnt the previous map in under a week purely due to the great landmark positioning.  Onto the community, which seems to have degraded somehow (even further from what it already was). Join a new server as a carnivore, and the first person to see you, be herbivore or carnivore, will kill you. See some dinosaurs of your own species? Run up to them and be killed immediately because they're hanging in a group of mixed carnivores and herbivores. Basically, no matter what you play as, and no matter what they are playing as, they'll kill you for sport. You're a baby utah, with 7 bodies lying around and they're an adult triceratops? They'll kill you. The community has gone from kosing (killing on sight) to pure ksf-ing (killing for sport). People go out of their way to end you, even heading straight for you like a torpedo if they've spotted you 2km away across a huge canyon, and even if they are a herbivore.  I don't get it, I don't understand it, and the fact that you can't speak to them before or while they pursue you and kill you is the most infuriating thing I have EVER encountered in a game in 23 years. This behaviour alone ruins the game for me. The anger you feel as you watch your sub Giga being chased and killed by an adult Para (or something equally pointless/ridiculous) for the 5th time in a row is unlike anything I've experienced in a video game.  I understand, its a survival game, or 'hardcore' survival game. And if I die 4 seconds before becoming an adult rex or similar, I'm fine with that, if it's because of my own mistakes. If it's because a pair of trikes hunted me across the map until I starved to death, then that's not ok. That's not how the game should be played, and it takes whatever fun is left in this game and punts it into oblivion. The new footprints in nightvision makes it impossible to run from anything. Are you 5 minutes away from becoming an adult rex after 4 hours of mind numbingly boring, stressful waiting? Bad luck, here comes a diablo to literally run you down until you are out of stamina, just to kill you for LITERALLY NO ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• REASON.  The new weather effects are super laggy. They're nice, the wet effects on the dinosaurs looks fantasic, the sound is incredible.. But when your 2017 Alienware can't run it without lagging, you've got problems. I went from running everything on cinematic at 60fps 3 months ago, to now running everything on high (2 down from cinematic) and still getting lag spikes at barely 30fps at the best of times. And it's due to the new weather effects.  Unfortunately my review is still a negative one. I'd hoped that the giant update would fix things, but after the excitement of the new map and new survival dinosaurs wore off, and all my friends stopped playing again to wait for the next update, all of the problems, new and old, started to creep through again. I really want to like this game, I want to love it. And sometimes I really do. But not enough, and the frustration and anger I get from this game 99% of the time just doesn't make up for that 1% of the time where I'm genuinly having fun.", "appid": "376210", "steamid": "profiles/76561198054916478", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "9", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1525089600.0}
