{"text": "There are a few good things about this game, but overall it gets dull, repetitive, and annoying quickly. The tutorials give you the basics of ship control but tell you absolutely nothing about what to do once you start actually playing. Direction is severely lacking in game but the community is fairly helpful. Combat is fun for a little bit but you will quickly realize that every engagement is going to end up with you spinning circles around each other while blasting each others faces off. Travel is tedious even with a ship that has a good jump range. It involves jumping from start to star which only requires the push of a button and about 5 seconds to line up the jump then you have to wait for a mini cutscene that is basically the same every time. \"FRAME SHIFT DRIVE CHARGING\" is my least favorite saying ever now. There was potential for this game, and maybe it will improve with time, but i can not recommend it currently.", "appid": "359320", "steamid": "profiles/76561197973607961", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1444564800.0}
