{"text": "It's one of my biggest gaming disappointments of 2017. I played it a bit on PS4 in 2017. Now I've just checked if something has changed during last 3 years and whether it is worth giving this game a second chance. It is not. Something has changed, but still too little to be worth investing time in this production. I've recently played five matches and I think it's a waste of time to play this game. Especially that there is UMvC3, which is much better, quite brilliant. Marvel vs. Capcom: Infinite will be remembered as a grim joke and spitting in the MvC series fans' faces. The game's mechanics are bizarre, boring, coarse. There are not many iconic heroes in the game, the characters models are nasty and the whole graphics (compared to other modern fighting games) is terribly tacky. Characters taunts are very dry, dialogues as well, and the whole mood is totally f**ked up. Overlook (this game) whenever possible.", "appid": "493840", "steamid": "profiles/76561198033142997", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "25", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1591876800.0}
