{"text": "be aware, though there is a way to get past this one bug in the game, unless you are aware of it before you play the game you have the chance of triggering it by not grabbing a particular item before another item.  If you do grab that item then you can't continue with the game and this happens about 2/3 rds into the game.  if you want to play this game go to the discussion board for this game to find the solution to avoid that bug before you play.  I won't post it in a review as that could be considered a spoiler.  If you still want to play the game it's an average Hidden object game.  I think if you purchase this one in a bundle or it's on sale on steam and it's a couple of bucks if you like to play hogs ( they have been my go to games for years when I just want to relax and play a game really casually) then go for it but it's pretty much your typical earlier style of HOG.    There are steam achievements if that is something you like.  There are not extras or in game achievements in this one.  Also there is no voice acting.  I forgot when this was made but I'm guessing early 2000's. puzzles the few they have are easy.  plenty of HOS sprinkled in the game.  travel map but it doesn't label the locations so I used the hint button more to just give me a location idea of where to go next so I wasn't clicking on the map going to the wrong area, to cut down wandering back and forth.   I played this through the first time I got this in 2017 but came up on the bug the second time around so be sure to read about that before you buy or try.", "appid": "396850", "steamid": "profiles/76561198149384609", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1603800000.0}
