{"text": "I really love Endless Space. Both Endless Space 1 and 2 are one of the best games out there. Sadly, I personally don't recommend the game (tl;dr at the bottom). I've never really been all too good at 4X games and usually do slight cheats to get an advantage; mainly because I don't actually take my time to learn the mechanics in detail. But I actually decided to put time into learning this game. So at one point I'm doing my first ever non-cheat session in a 4x game where I am doing very well and have created a powerful empire. Then, suddenly, my entire empire goes into rebellion without any warning or valid reason. This rebellion causes my empire to become a new form of government. The next turn, ANOTHER rebellion and government change. Then the next turn and the next. After over 10 turns it just doesn't stop. It's an infinite loop. Here's my post on the issue The 'bug' ruined the game for me. I explained in detail in the post above, but basically my enitre empire had no reason to go on a full blown rebellion since it was doing so well and the majority of my people were happy. It would have made sense for a few systems to rebel, not my entire empire. The worst part is that all you can do is sit there as everything falls apart. The issue appears to still be not fixed and is apparently considered a feature. I haven't touched the game ever since because it left a bad taste in my mouth and it would only occur again unless I decided to change my playstyle (same playstyle I have in all 4x games that I enoy). tl;dr: Bug in the game causes your ENTIRE empire/civ/whatever to go into an infinite rebellion loop every single turn out of no where without warning or valid reason just because of 1 or 2 unhappy colonies. Review will be Not Recommended until the issue is fixed.", "appid": "392110", "steamid": "profiles/76561198022696584", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": "4", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1520856000.0}
