{"text": "DO NOT BUY THIS GAME FOR MULTIPLAYER. Yeah, i got banned. You might think i'm bluffing about it and because i used mod so i got banned. But just hear me out : If i'm bluffing, or if the banned players were bluffing, why this is the only game that people bluffed the most, while other competitive games like CS:GO or PUBG, you rarely can see someone talk about it? I started playing Online from beginning of February or so, and got banned on 3rd March for 30 days, and until this day i still don't know what i did to get banned. It's really frustrating and hopeless to find your way out of the ban, since Rockstar is no longer accepting ban appeals, and don't expect to know the reason of your banned too because their EULAs said so. Another thing that annoys me is some of the modders, until this date, are not banned. Yeah, i've been digging into communities, asking peoples, and they still have mods opening in Online, and still not banned. I literally don't understand what Rockstar is and has been doing. I mean, after almost 3 years since the Online mode came out, they should have an Anti-cheat system that prevents people from spawning stuffs, being immortal like they're the host of the server, not banning players mistakenly and hopefully will get some cheaters out. I only got banned for 30 days, but after 30 days i definitely will not play this game again until they implemented some system that guarantees to wipe off the cheaters instead of normal players.", "appid": "271590", "steamid": "profiles/76561198261032304", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1520251200.0}
