{"text": "I do not precisely know what's the best point to watch upon this game. Do you like achievements? Ten minutes, maybe twenty, no more. You have just to visit all the locations - no, it's not that big - and purchase the costumes, do the voting thing and just keep on watching your autoclicker do its job. The Italian translation is one of the best I saw here on Steam. Every single time I wonder about who and how makes these translation. It's simply awesome. We have literally to \"accumulare il ritiro dalla nascita\". Which means something like \"accumulate the retreat from the beginning\". This seems more of an Italian war simulator, you know, we usually begin to think about switching sides before even starting the conflict. But probably something got lost in translation - maybe \"retirement\" in English, which translates to \"pensionamento\" in Italian? I don't really know how one should be supposed to retreat since he's born.. =P For the sake of having something fun in a negative review I chose to maintain the Italian language in-game too, being welcomed by a screen that tells me that Russia is the \"miglior paese per i restanti\". Something like \"the best country for those who stay\" (since \"restare\" is like, \"resta a casa\" with this COVID epidemics, \"stay at home\"!). Unluckily I've been to Russia and also many times to Ukraine and former USSR countries but I don't have that much experience so let's see what we can do here if we are \"restanti\" that accumulate \"ritiri\" from the start. Ok guys I'm just stopping here, it's clear that I'm just making fun of a long machine translated thing, if \"la tua zucca si risolve all'ospedale\" which literally means \"your head (\"zucca\" is quite vulgar =P) resolves in a hospital\" - in how much time? The graphics and overall the whole game is ridiculously designed, everything looks like it's been taken like Whatsapp stickers and put upon badly drawn backgrounds. We are greeted though with the awesome Russian anthem throughout the whole game. It repeats itself over and over, there are no other sounds apart some stupid effects. Somehow, I really love Slavic countries anyways. Definitely. My Cyrillic tattoo on my right arm puzzles many guys here in Northern Italy. And it's in Ukrainian, too. The game is just a pointless clicker, and as I said with a normal autoclicker you can clear everything easily. You simply get money by clicking and you can buy something like.. clothes and things to eat or something like that. So, with an autoclicker, you'll easily get all the money you'll need. Once you'll get to 100 rubles or whatever that is, you'll be able to buy a new background, basically. There's some of them, some \"stages\" in which nothing changes. You can change the \"skin\" of your clickable thing which goes basically from worst to even worst graphical content. Take a peek at all the screenshots I'm quite sad about the fact that this game has tons of fake reviews - i.e.: dozens of Italian reviews, for instance, all positive, made up by some words clearly machine-translated with lots of errors and made by fake accounts. Anyways. Summing everything up. It's a clicker, you'll be able to get all the achievements in less than half an hour with an autoclicker, and there's nothing funny or particularly amusing here. Just boring and without any kind of entertainment or replayability value since it's all about clicking and buying images of things. If you're European try to travel to the East and you'll find some of the most beautiful countries, cultures and people of the whole world. And I have no Slavic blood at all, but just trust me, visit everything there if you can! Don't buy this thing.", "appid": "1070330", "steamid": "profiles/76561198356141989", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "25", "votes_funny": "8", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1596283200.0}
