{"text": "I've played PUBG from the initial release date, and wow, would you look at that? I come back all the way at fall ever since the Spring release, and still, the net code is a tick rate of 17hz.  I still get the oh so   lag compensation system which gets me shot behind cover. The only things I've noticed new are a   frame rate improvement, and paid micro transactions   have snuck in. Alongside a few weapons which, to me, barely change the meta.  I'll give credit where it is due, I do highly approve of some of the frame rate improvements, though I do know the game on many systems still tends to run like hot manure and even can tend to feel slightly clunky on higher end systems, at least judging by input of my friends. I still enjoy the rush the game has, and the fun of the game stands out from the predecessors like the Arma mod and H1Z1. But it still has glaring issues that have needed attention since release.  The inevitable delay of things such as vaulting. And they want to release this game at the end of THIS YEAR. But they aren't addressing the fact that an RNG shooter, that has a tick rate that is below 30hz, is going be   and is to release. This game shouldn't even be REMOTELY close to an eSports shooter, or anything of the sort until this is ironed out.  With a tickrate of 17hz, the shooting may as well be as RNG as the looting and circle systems. To add salt to the wound, now there are more reports of PILES of hackers, more than there ever have been. People who genuinely put effort into make a dent on the leaderboards, climbing up, have to deal with this fact by losing their spots, whilst Bluehole sits away clearly not putting any action into this. I personally haven't encountered an extremely obvious hacker, but it is said that they are much more common as of today.  What baffles me is how this is the   played game in all of Steam, yet these glaring issues aren't being addressed WHATSOEVER. Instead of better server optimization, we get a vaulting system, which was already delayed. And a release at December these developers want? What a sick joke. More priority is being put into helping Twitch streamers not getting \"harassed\" by people with a honked horn 50 metres away.  Please, don't give these developers cash. They've tasted the greed, and clearly it has hit them hard judging by their development cycle. If you already own this game, show these developers that this is wrong.  I'm not saying I despise the game, I quite frankly adore it. It had the best enactment of Battle Royale we've had so far, not to feed into PlayerUnknown's latest narcissism. I shared the same opinion of DayZ, and I really do not want this game to end up like that. A money grab and a good abandon ship would be an absolute disappointment, and I really do hope they address these issues judging by all the reviews that have been posted.  I got this game via the means of a friend.  My hours may reflect that I haven't extensively played this game, but I do believe that 134 hours for the first month of the game's release and a good little break and another 30 or so hours of the past 3 weeks is more than enough fair judgement, especially since I review my older footage to compare details I noticed with the game with other present day recorded footage.", "appid": "578080", "steamid": "profiles/76561198040172996", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1509537600.0}
