{"text": "Season 1: Brilliant Season 2: Enjoyable Season Michonne: Unnecessary, pointless and poorly written. The story of Michonne is one that differs from the previous Telltale iterations of The Walking Dead, in that it revolves around a character already developed in the comics, a character who we know survives through the end of the game, due to her appearance in later comic issues. The game itself, tries to expand ever slightly on the gameplay that we have come to love, in the walking dead, yet ultimately fails to impress. The other characters themselves, fail to offer any sort of interesting qualities that would bring the player to become attached to them or become upset, should they be killed off.  Another piece that made the walking dead games so iconic is the drastic effects decision making can have regarding the life or death of a character. Choices in this game have little to no effect on the ultimate outcomes (in episode 1), and even if they did, as I mentioned, no one would care if a character dies. The real question is not whether or not this game is good, but whether or not we should really care about the characters, their stories or what occurs in the game.", "appid": "429570", "steamid": "profiles/76561198088660638", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "145", "votes_funny": "7", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1456920000.0}
