{"text": "I'm going to break this down very honestly, The \"Tutorial\" is a series of must play, unskippable missions where you have to run around the main town \"Hub\" of the game talking to people and doing little bits of gameplay for approximately 45 minutes before you can even actually attempt to play the game. All of which takes place after a fairly weak character creation. The servers are super laggy to the point where in a 4 hour period i was disconnected from the game and sent back to the main menu 8 times equating to 4 hours on steam record being closer to 2 hours including the 45 minute \"Tutorial\". When i was able to actually play the game it would lag out every 2-3 minutes resulting in people teleporting halfway accross the map and quite often falling to your death because you walked off a cliff after getting teleported back to a previous position with no chance to recover and save yourself or getting killed instantly by enemies that simply appeared next to you from half the map away. The game is very broken at the moment and almost completely unplayable, but when it does work the game is very smooth, with intense, heart-pounding, moment to moment action that you would expect from a franchise like naruto. If they fix the server issues and make it to where the game runs well and doesn't suffer from such excessive lag then the game has potential to be phenomenal! I hope this helps for anyone looking to get this game.", "appid": "633230", "steamid": "profiles/76561198232991136", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1536926400.0}
