{"text": "While the game seems charming at first, even interesting for it's exploration and progression...  that quickly stagnates.  You have only a few skills per class, and only two class type for each of the four (4) archetype.  Combat for your class is almost always the same, and for some using the \"run away to cheese your health back\" is a commonplace activity. Perhaps the worst part of the game is it's repetitiveness.  Once you \"clear\" the first zone, moving onto the second zone removes -all- your gear since it can't be used in other zones.  You have to quest in the new zone and find all NEW gear to use there.  Wash, rinse, repeat for each zone you go to. There are no building aspects, no campaign, and no end game - it is purely mini-missions to unlock loot rewards and some artifacts that allow you to unlock access to other items (or things like the hang glider or boat).  The artifacts are like all the gear - they go poof the moment you step into a new zone.  It's almost like Wollay (the primary developer) had an evil moment over the last six years and decided to region lock everything, wiping out all prior progression. You'll probably get 15 or 20 hours out of it wandering around and fighting stuff, reading wikis and watching videos on how to do things, where to go, how to tame pets, and so on.  But in the end, it's a rather unfulfilling experience due to being empty and highly repetitive. The original Alpha from 6 years ago was designed far better, and it's a shame that direction wasn't continued.  If you have a copy of that, play it instead.  Cubeworld clearly had a moment of greatness when it was in the spotlight and well-designed 6 years ago..  and it missed that mark when it waited those six years and changed dramatically, and for the worse. Cubeworld rating:  C- Best moments:  Finding Legendary gear, taming animals. Worst moments:  Beating a sector and moving to a new one, while losing all your items, regularly.", "appid": "1128000", "steamid": "profiles/76561197970676861", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "223", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1573905600.0}
