{"text": "When i first heard about this game i was pretty damn excited, since I've lived for dragons and dinosaurs since i was younger, and i already own The Isle and had been wondering about a dragon game similar to it for a while. I got it as soon as it was released and to be fair it was fun at first. I mainly played on a single server for around a week or two, leading groups of 20+ players across the desert to explore and navigate. It was honestly extremely fun and beautiful watching so many dragons flying together, like a scene from HTTYD. I made close friends in the game, met someone who is now very important to me, and generally had a good time. However, that is probably all the good that came from this game. From the start the idea of paying to play as different dragon species seemed questionable and a bit gross, as well as what had happened before the game was even released and the drama that continues to this day. Getting the game was only worth it for me because I met someone who i now love. It's buggy, probably shouldn't have been released when it was, and needed constant attention of in-game server admins who had to help people almost every 2 seconds. It is, as I've seen someone describe it as, a dumpster fire. The game has went from an average of 200+ players a day to barely scraping double digits over the entire server list. To top it off, the developer is all over the place and creates constant issues. I will hold out the hope that this game will improve one day, but until then i do not recommend you purchase and play this game unless you want to be disappointed.", "appid": "1088090", "steamid": "profiles/76561198366929836", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "28", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1581249600.0}
