{"text": "MUH BANNERLORD! It's missing something new and innovating. Lots of weird design decisions. Towns are rather dull and lacks atmosphere and polish, it's very quiet like it's missing tons of amient sounds. Music is nice but gets on your nerve when its played on repeat. Why not has something more ambient and subtle, to build immersion. Overall sound and music needs a lot of work still. where is all the quests and random encounters? They need to add some more events and dynamic behaviour to make it more interesting to replay. I can't imagining playing this over and over when it's so much the same. The world feels very empty, looters, caravans and lords is all you pretty much see. A lot of reused scenes and towns. Combat is decent but very much the same as Warband, AI seems to be rather broken at times. Companions get stuck, and armies moshpit with no tactics or realistic battle behaviour. I'm also not seeing much in the Crusader Kings 4x type content. Overall you should probably wait and see if they are willing to create something interesting here. EDIT:  It also randomly crash, making it unplayable at certain criterias. Lol the crash reporter is also bugged. Why does my arab character sound like a british hooligan? Breaks immersion. Some quests are really broken. They make the game crash no matter what. Quest giver: ERROR_COMMENT_STRING variable has not been set before. Game keeps crashing, so it's unplayable for some people. Not worth the money.", "appid": "261550", "steamid": "profiles/76561197961155896", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1585656000.0}
