{"text": "As of right now, I would not recommend this game. It has so much potential, but it is ruined by a few things. The thing that absolutely kills this game is the input lag. It's like there is a 50ms input lag to the mouse and keyboard when playing this game. It almost makes me feel sick when I'm playing it. They should at least add a raw mouse input option in the final version of the game to alleviate the issue. I'm using a 144Hz G-sync monitor, and I'm playing the game at very high frame rates with high-end hardware. So my setup is not the cause of the input lag. It's the game. Another thing that ruins this is the match-making. It is pretty bad. There is no server browser so you have to rely on match-making. It takes around 20 minutes just to find a North American server, but it only takes a few minutes to find a European server. So if you are playing in the U.S. expect a high ping and further lag on top of the input lag. Also, expect your match to crash to the main menu often, and the only way to start a new match is to exit the game and wait until the match that you were in ends. Also, when you crash to the main menu, most of the interface gets broken. I do like that there is a global chat box in the main menu because you're gonna need to talk to people to get some help on the game mechanincs. The tutorials aren't that good, and they don't go into the details of how everything works. Once you figure out how everything works and you start playing the game, it can get somewhat addicting. The final thing that ruins the game is the repair times for weapons and armor. I've seen it take up to 18 real hours just to repair a damaged weapon or armor, and you can't upgrade your weapons or armor until they are repaired. In order to get fast repair times you have to pay real money. Kinda greedy there. If it wasn't for those major issues, the game would actually be really good. The graphics are fairly decent with beautiful atmosphere. Some of the textures are really low-res though. Also, the weapon models and textures look really good as well. There are tons of free weapons in this game, and each of the four factions have their own weapon sets. You can also spend real money on premium weapons. This kinda makes the game a little unfair though. There are three team-based game modes to play right now. There is TDM, a conquest-style mode called \"Research\", and a mode where teams fight to collect all of the batteries before the other team does called \"Battery Retrieval\". I only got to play TDM and Research because they are the only modes that match-making would find for me. The maps are also pretty large. They aren't even close to the size of Battlefield maps, but Survarium's TDM maps are much bigger than Battlefield's TDM maps. Also, the anomalies in the game are just purely frustrating. They block access to many parts of each map, and they will kill you if you just barely get in the vicinity of them. If you get a high enough isolation percentage on your armor you can capture them, but be prepared to grind for 50+ hours just to get to that point. I think there is a faction that is immune to anomalies, so that makes the game extremely unbalanced right off the bat. Once you collect an anomaly, they can be used as perks during that match. I don't know how useful they are because I never got good enough armor to collect them. The only purposed they served as for me were colorful, route-blocking death objects. The game gets extremely frustrating if you get paired up with players that are two or more tiers higher than you are. If you are a tier three player going against a tier five player or higher, prepare to get owned. At that point the enemies just become bullet sponges, and it becomes impossible to get kills. The only way to truely enjoy this game is if you are playing with people that are in the same tier as you (or with people no more than one tier higher than you are). The game is also slightly pay-to-win, but it's not that bad. I've had lots of fun with this game, but I eventually got fed up with the input and server lag, so I unistalled it. I will definitely reinstall this game when it leaves early access though.", "appid": "355840", "steamid": "profiles/76561198004493133", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1436184000.0}
