{"text": "So after playing some hours and feeling really frustrated, i decided to write and share my experiences with the game A.I. and gameplay. For references sake i used the \"gold bundle\" First off it would be a great game if the A.I. actually was any good, alas as in most games all it does is cheat and screw around. it can't build a planet worth ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• so while having an edge in the early gamephase, later on the AI planets are not even 1/4 as good as yours. it keeps sending small/medium sized suicide fleets, so only annoying thing is taking all those down they don't pose any real threat. same goes for the ships the A.I. uses, those may be decent in the early game phase, but in late game they are just a waste of ressources. Usually planets are only defended by ships (even the legions are in transports), so all you need is one little troop carrier to take all planets with 0 losses after you destroyed those 2 - 3 defending ships.  i won't go into economy, but you can skip trade/income and just focus on tourism, basically 1 building per planet is all you ever gonna need, to have more cash as is possible to spend. The only challenge is surviving early game period, where i found myself being at the bottom of the food chain. Situation got reversed in late game, where its no fun declaring war as the outcome is guranteed victory with you being 10 times as strong as all others combined.  The gameplay is damn repetitive, i got bored after building up 100 planets and each time you conquer a new one, the first thing you have to do is scrap 90% of the buildings, as the previous buildup was just horrible. Most of the gametime you won't spend playing but allocating building queques to your planets, as the automanagement is just as bad.  Lastly i tried playing the campaign, but it doesn't include half the game features and the A.I. there is totally broken, it felt like it wasn't doing anything, neither your allies nor your enemies.", "appid": "226860", "steamid": "profil