{"text": "*Worth the read for any serious player / interested party* Current (v256.1) (2017-04-01) One of the worst updates and optimization I've seen in any game, and the update went live April 1st. (? :D Joke) With more Negitive Reviews on this game in less then 24 hours to drop \"Mostly Positive\" to \"Mixed\" and it's only going down hill until this joke gets put to rest. Roll back, once again. 36 Hours. Go back to brainstorming. (<--- Needs to be done) 50,000-70,000 Players avg online (day) 35,000-45,000 Players avg online (night) Probably more due to weekend + boosted rates on weekends and it's been dropping since the update, already below 30,000 Vaults ~ NO Flyers ~ NO Don't come out with a system that forces you to put months of work into  to completely tear it down with one update. (I.e breeding countless generations, thousands of hours, missed sleep, failed relationships) This is a failed attempt at A.) A Joke B.) Teleporter incentive  C.) Providing valid and useful content in anyway. Look at the mods. Look at what people, smart people, thoughtful people. People that play the game, know the game DO WITH THE GAME. First you take our Rockets. Then you rip up our prized Blueprints. And now, you replace our rustic HUD with this labyrinthine of useless information and then...sniff...sniff.. YOU CLIPPED THEM..OUR BIRDS....AND MADE PENS OR SOME ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• FOR HARRY POTTER FAN FICTION. Worst free game out there. Oh wait, it's not free I forgot, you needed to PAY to waste your time haha. If you're thinking about buying Ark, try waiting until the reviews get better. You'd have more fun clicking on *Link has Been Removed* then playing it right now. ________________________________________________________________________________ ________________________________________________________________________________ -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- ***New Info*** (Update Review) 2017-04-05 \"There were many PvP implications in flier speed, not only did it make snatching, C4 bombing, and Quetz Grenading huge, easy issues, but it had underlying repercussions in the overall pvp gameplay space with regards to trivializing the land dinos which we actually want to see in battle, and giving people the option to remain endlessly airborne with giant mobile chaingun/gatling/rocket platforms high above the world and out of range of any threats. There were also PvE implications. The ground game was essentially trivialized. You could live on the back of a Quetz perpetually after getting one, never even having to land... ever, really. 80% of the game was easily ignored because the air is safer, more straightforward, etc.\" The above was writin by the Senior Gameplay Designer. This is in regards to Flyers. However. You could say the same thing about rafts. You can stay on a Raft forever, ignoring the land and missing out on 80% of the game, or more. And you'd never, ever have to to go land. (Not true, as you'd need resources and food / water (if in air) and the latter if you were on a raft. What about all the bugs rafts made? Getting outside the map, spawning in players bases, cluttering up the map, glitching your items into the world ect. Having Flyers in the game, is the reason I bought the game. I'm fully aware of the fact this game is Early Access. However when I bought this game, Early Access was expected to end years ago, and this \"change\" that people are blaming on Early Access, happend long after the projected period that this game would be finished. Don't make items (I.e Clusters / Rocket / Mini Turrets) if they BREAK your game. \"in the overall pvp gameplay space with regards to trivializing the land dinos which we actually want to see in battle\" Anyone that has played SOTF (Old School) before Birds in that mode were nerfed about as hard as the game itself. Knows that Land Dinos win. Always. Without contest. Rex Level 10 Beats Rex Level 1. And So on. There is no skill in that. It's just who can tame the biggest and highest level Dino, or even in many cases breed the most god tier land Dino. And we can all agree it takes no skill to tame. Or very little (I should know, it's one of my favorite things to do) Flyers is the game. It's not just some \"Meta\" it's the whole game. The world, map, everything revolves around the ability to fly. That is how the game was made, and now they're saying since they've added new content (Like Cluster nades, Platform Saddles,  Rocket / Mini Turrets) that Flyers are broken. How about you look into the implication of thoses additions vs breaking your game. Land Dinos collect resources. But when you go and add Dinos, like  the Theri you break the whole chain. When is the last time anyone ever needed a Mammoth. Or a Berrie Collector. Or even a Meat Collector. Or Fiber Collector. Ape was a hard tame, hard to get one that can defend itself. (Fiber) Thatch (Weak tame, good for a single thing i.e thatch, and thats it) Beaver / Mammoth (Good for wood, Beaver serious out did the mammoth,  making it useless) (Then the pair were trumped by the Theri) Rex or any other meat collector. (Trumped by Theri) Even a low level 15 Theri leveled up into Power, can collect enough meat and battle 99% things in the south. As well as collect enough Fiber for a Alphas tribes needs.  You say you want to see Land Dinos in PVP and more use in PVE to prevent people from playing the game THEY WANT TO PLAY. The key word is \"You\" We don't need \"You\" to chose how we play an Open World / Sandbox game. If people want to sit in the sky, and rule the damn clouds, who the cares. Let them.  This is no longer a mystery it's a fact. They're trying to controll the way we play the game and I bought a Sandbox / Open World game. Not a Paint-By-Number. \"Open world, free roam, or (more loosely) sandbox are terms for video games where a player can move freely through a virtual world and is given considerable freedom in regard to how and when to approach particular objectives, as opposed to other video games that have a more linear structure to their gameplay\" You want to fix your game? Then do it. Just don't break the core gameplay of it as an attempt to fix your failed ideas and desires. You're breaking the foudation of your otherwise great game. And I won't beapart of it. Now lets see if I can get a refund on this game.", "appid": "346110", "steamid": "profiles/76561197966756586", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "798", "votes_funny": "60", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1491048000.0}
