{"text": "TLDR : Would I recommend a friend to buy a scam product? No! You get none of the content and interesting interactions that were promised by paradox. The game is a beta built, they didn't even include naval combat yet... that you're gonna have to pay the 1.1 DLC. Fans of Paradox give a pass to the \"release now, develop later\" business strategies, but I cannot. Because this will just encourage the corporate guys on top to give you even less on the next game release. Hell, continue giving it a pass and they'll start releasing games with only the title screen playable. Will it get better with time? Flip a coin, because there's no way anyone knows that as of today. Look at Stelaris, the hates gets bigger the more DLC they release. The same as been going on for the last 5 DLC of EU4. So even though fans would love you to buy the game on such a promise, it is a gamble. And that's not mentioning the price you'll have to pay. Gameplay wise, you can paint a map. Nothing matters until they get disloyal, do a click and the situation is fixed and then get to conquering some more. You can't interact with other nations in any other way sooooo.  And to go to war you just have to wait for points to go up every month and use it to justify your war. You have no control of the point generation speed. The justify action cost 200 points at point generation during the campaign averages 6 per month. This requires you to wait almost three years to justify 1 war on 1 nation that could be 1 city at most. the Game has thousands of cities and you have 277 years to do it. Good luck", "appid": "859580", "steamid": "profiles/76561198007802543", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "10", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1557835200.0}
