{"text": "I have never hated a video game more in my entire life.  I hate this game with a BURNING passion. I've 100%ed over a thousand games - sometimes extremely difficult, horrible, painful, brutal roguelikes and such.  Games that took me many more hours and grind than this game should take.  But nothing compares to the agony of MHW and my infinite hatred for how mind-meltingly painful the end-game grinding for crowns is.  This is without a single doubt in my mind the WORST achievement to have ever been created on Earth. The game is fine for the first 60-70 hours, but then you hit the \"end-game\".  Crown hunting is a total RNG crapshoot.  You spend literally hundreds of hours just entering and leaving investigation missions, trying to measure yourself up against the leg of some massive creature and determine if it is 25% smaller or larger than \"average\".  You do this merely by eyeballing it because the game doesn't provide any in-game measurement.  You do this dozens of times, back to back to back to back.  With the slowest multi-key menus ever.  And if it seems close enough to the size you need, then you kill it, with all the stress of knowing that if you mess up, you've wasted it and will need to grind for many hours again.  And after you kill one you wait for minutes again just to see if it was RNG big/small enough after the mission. This game has no-joke given me depression for the first time in my life.  I stay at work in my office late, dreading to come home, because I know MHW is there.  I consistently have nightmares about it when I sleep.  It drains me of happiness and energy for the entire day any day that I attempt to grind some more.  I woke up today at 9am and played it all day long and I didn't find a SINGLE crown that I needed.  I know I should just quit, and give up getting 100% in this game... I've not completed many other games, and I don't consider myself someone truly \"obsessed\" with getting 100% in everything.  I should seriously really just quit torturing myself.   This crown grind is ruining my relationships, ruining my 24/7 happiness... ruining my life.  The entire idea of an achievement like this is just so wrong - it literally incentives you to either play fully solo or to jump into random SOS missions, and then abandon them once you determine the monster is not an appropriate size, leaving those MP players with a harder version of the monster and no teammate to back them up.  Whoever created this crown stuff and achievement did not put nearly enough thought into it.  The game is so painfully slow, you have to confirm every button you click a second time and all the slow, mandatory wait period animations just build up onto you. I wish I never heard of this game, I wish I never bought this game.  I wish I could take it all back because I've never seen myself brought this low by anything.  I just want to be free.  I don't even know who I am anymore.  I hate Monster Hunter and I will NEVER play another MH game because of this. STRONGLY avoid this game if you even care a tiny bit about achievements.  I have never hated something more in my life.", "appid": "582010", "steamid": "profiles/76561197983791150", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "27", "votes_funny": "44", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1538308800.0}
