{"text": "TL;DR: Game plays like UNO, but is broken. Game crashes, game hosting is buggy and sucks, easy to play (obviously). Better off keeping your wallet away from this game. Sauce: The game is as it is; UNO. It's fun and great to play with friends... if you can get it to work all the time. Hosting a game is not hard, but inviting friends to play can bug out to where friends are in, but the host cannot see that they're in the lobby until they start the game. Sometimes, the game will crash for no good reason during a match, and you cannot join back in to continue the game you were previously in. Singleplayer is fine as is, although did not play it as much, because I got this game to play with friends, rather than to play by myself.  Overall (even though this wasn't a very thorough nor long explanation/review), the game is fun when it works. Although the game is not worth the $10 (even though I got it during the winter sale for $3). There are browser version of UNO that play and work better than this game, and are free. However I see that it's bound that there will be/is little-to-no further development toward this game, so save yourself some money, and play online in a browser, or buy the physical cards for about $6.", "appid": "470220", "steamid": "profiles/76561198094025520", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1546171200.0}
