{"text": "And in spectacular fashion, I decided to pick up a game that looked somewhat interesting to me in concept, Pratagon. An FPS Moba...could be good, if done right.  I had to check the Steam page to see if this was released as an early access title. Nope, sure enough, it's a full fledged released game. This is easily one of the worst games I've ever played. There is no soundtrack, everything is a free asset, and it's just an all around garbage fest.  The first time was for five minutes, I just put it on and jumped in to a bot match and started playing. I had the thought that there was no way it could be this bad, and that I must've been hungry, so I ate a slice of pizza and decided to delve into the settings menu. After looking through everything I could and trying everything I could to make it more playable and better looking, I discovered... ...that it was still one of the worst friggin' games I've ever played.  I mean it. If you land on a jump pad, there is a 50% chance that it will fling you into space, or that it will raise you to a reasonable height. When you hold down shift to sprint, it just continually accelerates. This has the effect of launching you off of platforms that you can stand on to attack the power crystals, enemies, or anything else that's trying to kill you first. It has the effect of making it feel like you're skating without any friction from the ground or floor to slow you down in any way. It's fun to play around with for about 13 seconds, and then you want to just exit the game as soon as possible.  Did I mention you can defeat your enemies and defeat the enemy turrets? It takes a good half an hour to defeat one enemy, and their accuracy is way better than yours, but it   be done.  Absolutely the worst, most uncomfortable accuracy I've ever seen in any game ever, and I've played some   games, people! Sure your shots land, and you can aim, but the actual movement of your projectiles is so slow that it creates a disorienting effect that you'll never get past. The special attacks also look like someone took an oval tool in Paint in Windows 3.1 and made the background clear later.  I felt the soundtrack was great, but mostly because there just wasn't any music at all and all you got to hear was PEWPEWPEWPEWPEPWEPWEPWEPWEPWEPWEPWPEWPWPEWPPWEPWEPWEPWEPWEPWPWPEWPEPWEPWEPWEPWEPWEPWPEWPEPWEPPEWPEWPEWPEWPEW from your laser, uh, P90, I guess?  Everything about this is a huge confusing mess, and I can't fathom how any developer could put this on Steam as a full release game and try to make money off of it. I should also point out that I'm NOT hard to please, my only requirements are basically that a game is fun and that it works, but this is, frankly, just awful. Don't buy it.", "appid": "950780", "steamid": "profiles/76561198091033148", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1541073600.0}
