{"text": "For 0.1.0 version: One of a few games that I refunded even though I really loved the original Rogue Legacy and I played through it three times.  - quite a lot of traits are annoying and there are too many of those that mess with your screen in some way, often making combination of class + trait nearly unplayable. Honestly cooldown on attack for barbarian when you wait 3-5 seconds to auto-attack again or Archer that doesn't see enemies due to 90% of screen being black? How fun is that? it isn't.  - there isn't much of the game honestly. Most of the enemies are just RL1 ones with new graphics. - No mouse lock to the window - 3 of my runs ended because my mouse moved to the second monitor, game switched focus and didn't pause. How that got past internal testing is beyond me. - next update is in 2 months according to the menu. That is incredibly long time for how little there is - Early Access exclusive challenge - this sets up a dangerous precedent that may become industry standart. It doesn't matter how small it but it is dangerous if it catchs on.  - No voice acting again and so far it feels like the same story recycled from RL1 - The preview videos show several classes and locations that are not in EA which isn't stated anywhere - EA was released with gamebreaking bugs - rooms impossible to finish, delay on auto-attack, falling through floor ... all of those are confirmed to be patched, but still Right now I feel like there is no reason to pick Rogue Legacy 2 over games like Hades or Hollow Knight which offer marginally better value for the same price. The Rogue-lite genre improved since the first game came out and yet this feels outdated even now. Also note: Games should be evaluated on current content and what they offer for your money, not \"Thumb up, no content, but it is ok because Early access, hur dur!\" which are most of the possitive reviews", "appid": "1253920", "steamid": "profiles/76561198004625267", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "76", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1597752000.0}
{"text": "Best Friend Forever is a visual novel dating sim coupled with dogs, sound like a winner right? Unfortunately what looks good on paper is executed poorly here.  The gameplay of Best Friend Forever is a very generic point and click dating story where you take of dogs in between. The characters are dull and the dialouges downright cringeworthy sometimes. The romances are also not given time to build up and feels extremely rushed. It took me around 2 hours to complete a selected route while taking care of the dog activities. Speaking ofdog activities, the dog part of the game feels tacked on just to appeal to more people. The care you take of your dogs does not effect the game in any significant way and its purely added for the sake of it. Since the characters are mostly bland, the short journey you take through the game is also farily bland. There is no spark between characters or a real feeling releatonship between you and your dog and it ends before it starts so the gameplay here is not good.  Visually Best Friend Forever, in my opinion, is not good. It goes for a cutesy artstyle but most of the characters and animations come off as jarring to say the least. The only thing I liked about the visuals here are the backgrounds and they are usually covered off by some bad looking characters. Some people might like this kind of visual style, it simply does not look good to me. Like the rest of the game, fairly generic. It does its job but you won‚Äôt remember it after the game is over. For this price tag, you can do far better than Best Friend Forever. It is short, generic, characters are bland and the story is incredibly rushed. It‚Äôs better to look for something else as there are far superior dating sims available for the same price.  This Review was brought to you by    ''If you liked this review and you want to get in touch with us, mail to contact@dnbmedia.co to get your game reviewed or promoted''", "appid": "1034850", "steamid": "profiles/76561198130657097", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1602072000.0}
